81constexpr bool IsOSR(BytecodeOffset osr_offset) { return !osr_offset.IsNone(); }
82
83class CompilerTracer : public AllStatic {
84 public:
85 static void TraceStartBaselineCompile(
86 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
87 if (!v8_flags.trace_baseline) return;
88 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
89 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "compiling method", shared, CodeKind::BASELINE);
90 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
91 }
92
93 static void TraceStartMaglevCompile(Isolate* isolate,
94 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
95 bool osr, ConcurrencyMode mode) {
96 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
97 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
98 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "compiling method", function, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
99 if (osr) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
100 PrintF(scope.file(), ", mode: %s", ToString(mode));
101 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
102 }
103
104 static void TracePrepareJob(Isolate* isolate, OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
105 ConcurrencyMode mode) {
106 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt || !info->IsOptimizing()) return;
107 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
108 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "compiling method", info);
109 if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
110 PrintF(scope.file(), ", mode: %s", ToString(mode));
111 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
112 }
113
114 static void TraceOptimizeOSRStarted(Isolate* isolate,
115 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
116 BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
117 ConcurrencyMode mode) {
118 if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
119 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
120 PrintF(
121 scope.file(),
122 "[OSR - compilation started. function: %s, osr offset: %d, mode: %s]\n",
123 function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt(), ToString(mode));
124 }
125
126 static void TraceOptimizeOSRFinished(Isolate* isolate,
127 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
128 BytecodeOffset osr_offset) {
129 if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
130 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
131 PrintF(scope.file(),
132 "[OSR - compilation finished. function: %s, osr offset: %d]\n",
133 function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt());
134 }
135
136 static void TraceOptimizeOSRAvailable(Isolate* isolate,
137 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
138 BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
139 ConcurrencyMode mode) {
140 if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
141 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
142 PrintF(scope.file(),
143 "[OSR - available (compilation completed or cache hit). function: "
144 "%s, osr offset: %d, mode: %s]\n",
145 function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt(), ToString(mode));
146 }
147
148 static void TraceOptimizeOSRUnavailable(Isolate* isolate,
149 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
150 BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
151 ConcurrencyMode mode) {
152 if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
153 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
154 PrintF(scope.file(),
155 "[OSR - unavailable (failed or in progress). function: %s, osr "
156 "offset: %d, mode: %s]\n",
157 function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt(), ToString(mode));
158 }
159
160 static void TraceFinishTurbofanCompile(Isolate* isolate,
161 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
162 double ms_creategraph,
163 double ms_optimize,
164 double ms_codegen) {
165 DCHECK(v8_flags.trace_opt);
166 DCHECK(info->IsOptimizing());
167 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
168 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed compiling", info);
169 if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
170 PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f, %0.3f, %0.3f ms", ms_creategraph,
171 ms_optimize, ms_codegen);
172 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
173 }
174
175 static void TraceFinishBaselineCompile(
176 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
177 double ms_timetaken) {
178 if (!v8_flags.trace_baseline) return;
179 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
180 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed compiling", shared, CodeKind::BASELINE);
181 PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f ms", ms_timetaken);
182 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
183 }
184
185 static void TraceFinishMaglevCompile(Isolate* isolate,
186 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
187 bool osr, double ms_prepare,
188 double ms_execute, double ms_finalize) {
189 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
190 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
191 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed compiling", function, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
192 if (osr) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
193 PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f, %0.3f, %0.3f ms", ms_prepare,
194 ms_execute, ms_finalize);
195 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
196 }
197
198 static void TraceAbortedMaglevCompile(Isolate* isolate,
199 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
200 BailoutReason bailout_reason) {
201 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
202 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
203 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "aborted compiling", function, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
204 PrintF(scope.file(), " because: %s", GetBailoutReason(bailout_reason));
205 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
206 }
207
208 static void TraceCompletedJob(Isolate* isolate,
209 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info) {
210 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
211 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
212 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed optimizing", info);
213 if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
214 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
215 }
216
217 static void TraceAbortedJob(Isolate* isolate, OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
218 double ms_prepare, double ms_execute,
219 double ms_finalize) {
220 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
221 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
222 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "aborted optimizing", info);
223 if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
224 PrintF(scope.file(), " because: %s",
225 GetBailoutReason(info->bailout_reason()));
226 PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f, %0.3f, %0.3f ms", ms_prepare,
227 ms_execute, ms_finalize);
228 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
229 }
230
231 static void TraceOptimizedCodeCacheHit(Isolate* isolate,
232 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
233 BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
234 CodeKind code_kind) {
235 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
236 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
237 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "found optimized code for", function, code_kind);
238 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
239 PrintF(scope.file(), " at OSR bytecode offset %d", osr_offset.ToInt());
240 }
241 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
242 }
243
244 static void TraceOptimizeForAlwaysOpt(Isolate* isolate,
245 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
246 CodeKind code_kind) {
247 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
248 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
249 PrintTracePrefix(scope, "optimizing", function, code_kind);
250 PrintF(scope.file(), " because --always-turbofan");
251 PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
252 }
253
254 static void TraceMarkForAlwaysOpt(Isolate* isolate,
255 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
256 if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
257 CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
258 PrintF(scope.file(), "[marking ");
259 ShortPrint(*function, scope.file());
260 PrintF(scope.file(),
261 " for optimized recompilation because --always-turbofan");
262 PrintF(scope.file(), "]\n");
263 }
264
265 private:
266 static void PrintTracePrefix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope,
267 const char* header,
268 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info) {
269 PrintTracePrefix(scope, header, info->closure(), info->code_kind());
270 }
271
272 static void PrintTracePrefix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope,
273 const char* header,
274 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
275 CodeKind code_kind) {
276 PrintF(scope.file(), "[%s ", header);
277 ShortPrint(*function, scope.file());
278 PrintF(scope.file(), " (target %s)", CodeKindToString(code_kind));
279 }
280
281 static void PrintTracePrefix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope,
282 const char* header,
283 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
284 CodeKind code_kind) {
285 PrintF(scope.file(), "[%s ", header);
286 ShortPrint(*shared, scope.file());
287 PrintF(scope.file(), " (target %s)", CodeKindToString(code_kind));
288 }
289
290 static void PrintTraceSuffix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope) {
291 PrintF(scope.file(), "]\n");
292 }
293};

297// static
298void Compiler::LogFunctionCompilation(Isolate* isolate,
299 LogEventListener::CodeTag code_type,
300 DirectHandle<Script> script,
301 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
302 DirectHandle<FeedbackVector> vector,
303 Handle<AbstractCode> abstract_code,
304 CodeKind kind, double time_taken_ms) {
305 DCHECK_NE(*abstract_code,
306 Cast<AbstractCode>(*BUILTIN_CODE(isolate, CompileLazy)));
307
308 // Log the code generation. If source information is available include
309 // script name and line number. Check explicitly whether logging is
310 // enabled as finding the line number is not free.
311 if (!isolate->IsLoggingCodeCreation()) return;
312
313 Script::PositionInfo info;
314 Script::GetPositionInfo(script, shared->StartPosition(), &info);
315 int line_num = info.line + 1;
316 int column_num = info.column + 1;
317 Handle<String> script_name(IsString(script->name())
318 ? Cast<String>(script->name())
319 : ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_string(),
320 isolate);
321 LogEventListener::CodeTag log_tag =
322 V8FileLogger::ToNativeByScript(code_type, *script);
323 PROFILE(isolate, CodeCreateEvent(log_tag, abstract_code, shared, script_name,
324 line_num, column_num));
325 if (!vector.is_null()) {
326 LOG(isolate, FeedbackVectorEvent(*vector, *abstract_code));
327 }
328 if (!v8_flags.log_function_events) return;
329
330 std::string name;
331 switch (kind) {
332 case CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION:
333 name = "interpreter";
334 break;
335 case CodeKind::BASELINE:
336 name = "baseline";
337 break;
338 case CodeKind::MAGLEV:
339 name = "maglev";
340 break;
341 case CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS:
342 name = "turbofan";
343 break;
344 default:
345 UNREACHABLE();
346 }
347 switch (code_type) {
348 case LogEventListener::CodeTag::kEval:
349 name += "-eval";
350 break;
351 case LogEventListener::CodeTag::kScript:
352 case LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction:
353 break;
354 default:
355 UNREACHABLE();
356 }
357
358 DirectHandle<String> debug_name =
359 SharedFunctionInfo::DebugName(isolate, shared);
360 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
361 LOG(isolate, FunctionEvent(name.c_str(), script->id(), time_taken_ms,
362 shared->StartPosition(), shared->EndPosition(),
363 *debug_name));
364}

367
368ScriptOriginOptions OriginOptionsForEval(
369 Tagged<Object> script, ParsingWhileDebugging parsing_while_debugging) {
370 bool is_shared_cross_origin =
371 parsing_while_debugging == ParsingWhileDebugging::kYes;
372 bool is_opaque = false;
373 if (IsScript(script)) {
374 auto script_origin_options = Cast<Script>(script)->origin_options();
375 if (script_origin_options.IsSharedCrossOrigin()) {
376 is_shared_cross_origin = true;
377 }
378 if (script_origin_options.IsOpaque()) {
379 is_opaque = true;
380 }
381 }
382 return ScriptOriginOptions(is_shared_cross_origin, is_opaque);
383}

390CompilationJob::Status UnoptimizedCompilationJob::ExecuteJob() {
391 // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
392 DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToExecute);
393 base::ScopedTimer t(v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken_to_execute_
394 : nullptr);
395 return UpdateState(ExecuteJobImpl(), State::kReadyToFinalize);
396}

398CompilationJob::Status UnoptimizedCompilationJob::FinalizeJob(
399 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info, Isolate* isolate) {
400 DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
401 DisallowCodeDependencyChange no_dependency_change;
402 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
403
404 // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
405 DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToFinalize);
406 base::ScopedTimer t(v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken_to_finalize_
407 : nullptr);
408 return UpdateState(FinalizeJobImpl(shared_info, isolate), State::kSucceeded);
409}

411CompilationJob::Status UnoptimizedCompilationJob::FinalizeJob(
412 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info, LocalIsolate* isolate) {
413 // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
414 DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToFinalize);
415 base::ScopedTimer t(v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken_to_finalize_
416 : nullptr);
417 return UpdateState(FinalizeJobImpl(shared_info, isolate), State::kSucceeded);
418}

420namespace {
421void LogUnoptimizedCompilation(Isolate* isolate,
422 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
423 LogEventListener::CodeTag code_type,
424 base::TimeDelta time_taken_to_execute,
425 base::TimeDelta time_taken_to_finalize) {
426 Handle<AbstractCode> abstract_code;
427 if (shared->HasBytecodeArray()) {
428 abstract_code =
429 handle(Cast<AbstractCode>(shared->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)), isolate);
430 } else {
431#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
432 DCHECK(shared->HasAsmWasmData());
433 abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(BUILTIN_CODE(isolate, InstantiateAsmJs));
434#else
435 UNREACHABLE();
436#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
437 }
438
439 double time_taken_ms = time_taken_to_execute.InMillisecondsF() +
440 time_taken_to_finalize.InMillisecondsF();
441
442 DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate);
443 Compiler::LogFunctionCompilation(
444 isolate, code_type, script, shared, DirectHandle<FeedbackVector>(),
445 abstract_code, CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION, time_taken_ms);
446}

484GlobalHandleVector<Map> OptimizedCompilationJob::CollectRetainedMaps(
485 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Code> code) {
486 DCHECK(code->is_optimized_code());
487
488 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
489 GlobalHandleVector<Map> maps(isolate->heap());
490 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
491 int const mode_mask = RelocInfo::EmbeddedObjectModeMask();
492 for (RelocIterator it(*code, mode_mask); !it.done(); it.next()) {
493 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsEmbeddedObjectMode(it.rinfo()->rmode()));
494 Tagged<HeapObject> target_object = it.rinfo()->target_object(cage_base);
495 if (code->IsWeakObjectInOptimizedCode(target_object)) {
496 if (IsMap(target_object, cage_base)) {
497 maps.Push(Cast<Map>(target_object));
498 }
499 }
500 }
501 return maps;
502}
503
504void OptimizedCompilationJob::RegisterWeakObjectsInOptimizedCode(
505 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> context,
506 DirectHandle<Code> code, GlobalHandleVector<Map> maps) {
507 isolate->heap()->AddRetainedMaps(context, std::move(maps));
508 code->set_can_have_weak_objects(true);
509}

525void TurbofanCompilationJob::RecordCompilationStats(ConcurrencyMode mode,
526 Isolate* isolate) const {
527 DCHECK(compilation_info()->IsOptimizing());
528 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = compilation_info()->shared_info();
529 if (v8_flags.trace_opt || v8_flags.trace_opt_stats) {
530 double ms_creategraph = time_taken_to_prepare_.InMillisecondsF();
531 double ms_optimize = time_taken_to_execute_.InMillisecondsF();
532 double ms_codegen = time_taken_to_finalize_.InMillisecondsF();
533 if (v8_flags.trace_opt) {
534 CompilerTracer::TraceFinishTurbofanCompile(
535 isolate, compilation_info(), ms_creategraph, ms_optimize, ms_codegen);
536 }
537 if (v8_flags.trace_opt_stats) {
538 static double compilation_time = 0.0;
539 static int compiled_functions = 0;
540 static int code_size = 0;
541
542 compilation_time += (ms_creategraph + ms_optimize + ms_codegen);
543 compiled_functions++;
544 code_size += shared->SourceSize();
545 PrintF(
546 "[turbofan] Compiled: %d functions with %d byte source size in "
547 "%fms.\n",
548 compiled_functions, code_size, compilation_time);
549 }
550 }
551 // Don't record samples from machines without high-resolution timers,
552 // as that can cause serious reporting issues. See the thread at
553 // http://g/chrome-metrics-team/NwwJEyL8odU/discussion for more details.
554 if (!base::TimeTicks::IsHighResolution()) return;
555
556 int elapsed_microseconds = static_cast<int>(ElapsedTime().InMicroseconds());
557 Counters* const counters = isolate->counters();
558 counters->turbofan_ticks()->AddSample(static_cast<int>(
559 compilation_info()->tick_counter().CurrentTicks() / 1000));
560
561 if (compilation_info()->is_osr()) {
562 counters->turbofan_osr_prepare()->AddSample(
563 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_prepare_.InMicroseconds()));
564 counters->turbofan_osr_execute()->AddSample(
565 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_execute_.InMicroseconds()));
566 counters->turbofan_osr_finalize()->AddSample(
567 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_finalize_.InMicroseconds()));
568 counters->turbofan_osr_total_time()->AddSample(elapsed_microseconds);
569 return;
570 }
571
572 DCHECK(!compilation_info()->is_osr());
573 counters->turbofan_optimize_prepare()->AddSample(
574 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_prepare_.InMicroseconds()));
575 counters->turbofan_optimize_execute()->AddSample(
576 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_execute_.InMicroseconds()));
577 counters->turbofan_optimize_finalize()->AddSample(
578 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_finalize_.InMicroseconds()));
579 counters->turbofan_optimize_total_time()->AddSample(elapsed_microseconds);
580
581 // Compute foreground / background time.
582 base::TimeDelta time_background;
583 base::TimeDelta time_foreground =
584 time_taken_to_prepare_ + time_taken_to_finalize_;
585 switch (mode) {
586 case ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent:
587 time_background += time_taken_to_execute_;
588 counters->turbofan_optimize_concurrent_total_time()->AddSample(
589 elapsed_microseconds);
590 break;
591 case ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous:
592 counters->turbofan_optimize_non_concurrent_total_time()->AddSample(
593 elapsed_microseconds);
594 time_foreground += time_taken_to_execute_;
595 break;
596 }
597 counters->turbofan_optimize_total_background()->AddSample(
598 static_cast<int>(time_background.InMicroseconds()));
599 counters->turbofan_optimize_total_foreground()->AddSample(
600 static_cast<int>(time_foreground.InMicroseconds()));
601
602 if (v8_flags.profile_guided_optimization &&
603 shared->cached_tiering_decision() ==
604 CachedTieringDecision::kEarlyMaglev) {
605 shared->set_cached_tiering_decision(CachedTieringDecision::kEarlyTurbofan);
606 }
607}
608
609void TurbofanCompilationJob::RecordFunctionCompilation(
610 LogEventListener::CodeTag code_type, Isolate* isolate) const {
611 Handle<AbstractCode> abstract_code =
612 Cast<AbstractCode>(compilation_info()->code());
613
614 double time_taken_ms = time_taken_to_prepare_.InMillisecondsF() +
615 time_taken_to_execute_.InMillisecondsF() +
616 time_taken_to_finalize_.InMillisecondsF();
617
618 DirectHandle<Script> script(
619 Cast<Script>(compilation_info()->shared_info()->script()), isolate);
620 DirectHandle<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector(
621 compilation_info()->closure()->feedback_vector(), isolate);
622 Compiler::LogFunctionCompilation(
623 isolate, code_type, script, compilation_info()->shared_info(),
624 feedback_vector, abstract_code, compilation_info()->code_kind(),
625 time_taken_ms);
626}
627
628uint64_t TurbofanCompilationJob::trace_id() const {
629 // Xor together the this pointer and the optimization id, to try to make the
630 // id more unique on platforms where just the `this` pointer is likely to be
631 // reused.
632 return reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(this) ^
633 compilation_info_->optimization_id();
634}

641#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
642bool UseAsmWasm(FunctionLiteral* literal, bool asm_wasm_broken) {
643 // Check whether asm.js validation is enabled.
644 if (!v8_flags.validate_asm) return false;
645
646 // Modules that have validated successfully, but were subsequently broken by
647 // invalid module instantiation attempts are off limit forever.
648 if (asm_wasm_broken) return false;
649
650 // In stress mode we want to run the validator on everything.
651 if (v8_flags.stress_validate_asm) return true;
652
653 // In general, we respect the "use asm" directive.
654 return literal->scope()->IsAsmModule();
655}
656#endif
657
658} // namespace
659
660void Compiler::InstallInterpreterTrampolineCopy(
661 Isolate* isolate, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
662 LogEventListener::CodeTag log_tag) {
663 DCHECK(isolate->interpreted_frames_native_stack());
664 if (!IsBytecodeArray(shared_info->GetTrustedData(isolate))) {
665 DCHECK(!shared_info->HasInterpreterData(isolate));
666 return;
667 }
668 DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array(
669 shared_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate), isolate);
670
671 Handle<Code> code =
672 Builtins::CreateInterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling(isolate);
673
674 DirectHandle<InterpreterData> interpreter_data =
675 isolate->factory()->NewInterpreterData(bytecode_array, code);
676
677 if (shared_info->HasBaselineCode()) {
678 shared_info->baseline_code(kAcquireLoad)
679 ->set_bytecode_or_interpreter_data(*interpreter_data);
680 } else {
681 // IsBytecodeArray
682 shared_info->set_interpreter_data(isolate, *interpreter_data);
683 }
684
685 DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()), isolate);
686 Handle<AbstractCode> abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(code);
687 Script::PositionInfo info;
688 Script::GetPositionInfo(script, shared_info->StartPosition(), &info);
689 int line_num = info.line + 1;
690 int column_num = info.column + 1;
691 Handle<String> script_name =
692 handle(IsString(script->name()) ? Cast<String>(script->name())
693 : ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_string(),
694 isolate);
695 PROFILE(isolate, CodeCreateEvent(log_tag, abstract_code, shared_info,
696 script_name, line_num, column_num));
697}

701template <typename IsolateT>
702void InstallUnoptimizedCode(UnoptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
703 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
704 IsolateT* isolate) {
705 if (compilation_info->has_bytecode_array()) {
706 DCHECK(!shared_info->HasBytecodeArray()); // Only compiled once.
707 DCHECK(!compilation_info->has_asm_wasm_data());
708 DCHECK(!shared_info->HasFeedbackMetadata());
709
710#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
711 // If the function failed asm-wasm compilation, mark asm_wasm as broken
712 // to ensure we don't try to compile as asm-wasm.
713 if (compilation_info->literal()->scope()->IsAsmModule()) {
714 shared_info->set_is_asm_wasm_broken(true);
715 }
716#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
717
718 DirectHandle<FeedbackMetadata> feedback_metadata = FeedbackMetadata::New(
719 isolate, compilation_info->feedback_vector_spec());
720 shared_info->set_feedback_metadata(*feedback_metadata, kReleaseStore);
721
722 shared_info->set_age(0);
723 shared_info->set_bytecode_array(*compilation_info->bytecode_array());
724 } else {
725#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
726 DCHECK(compilation_info->has_asm_wasm_data());
727 // We should only have asm/wasm data when finalizing on the main thread.
728 DCHECK((std::is_same<IsolateT, Isolate>::value));
729 shared_info->set_asm_wasm_data(*compilation_info->asm_wasm_data());
730 shared_info->set_feedback_metadata(
731 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_feedback_metadata(), kReleaseStore);
732#else
733 UNREACHABLE();
734#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
735 }
736}
737
738template <typename IsolateT>
739void EnsureInfosArrayOnScript(DirectHandle<Script> script,
740 ParseInfo* parse_info, IsolateT* isolate) {
741 DCHECK(parse_info->flags().is_toplevel());
742 if (script->infos()->length() > 0) {
743 DCHECK_EQ(script->infos()->length(), parse_info->max_info_id() + 1);
744 return;
745 }
746 DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> infos(isolate->factory()->NewWeakFixedArray(
747 parse_info->max_info_id() + 1, AllocationType::kOld));
748 script->set_infos(*infos);
749}

751void UpdateSharedFunctionFlagsAfterCompilation(FunctionLiteral* literal) {
752 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = *literal->shared_function_info();
753 DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->language_mode(), literal->language_mode());
754
755 // These fields are all initialised in ParseInfo from the SharedFunctionInfo,
756 // and then set back on the literal after parse. Hence, they should already
757 // match.
758 DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->requires_instance_members_initializer(),
759 literal->requires_instance_members_initializer());
760 DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->class_scope_has_private_brand(),
761 literal->class_scope_has_private_brand());
762 DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->has_static_private_methods_or_accessors(),
763 literal->has_static_private_methods_or_accessors());
764
765 shared_info->set_has_duplicate_parameters(
766 literal->has_duplicate_parameters());
767 shared_info->UpdateAndFinalizeExpectedNofPropertiesFromEstimate(literal);
768
769 shared_info->SetScopeInfo(*literal->scope()->scope_info());
770}

772// Finalize a single compilation job. This function can return
773// RETRY_ON_MAIN_THREAD if the job cannot be finalized off-thread, in which case
774// it should be safe to call it again on the main thread with the same job.
775template <typename IsolateT>
776CompilationJob::Status FinalizeSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
777 UnoptimizedCompilationJob* job, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
778 IsolateT* isolate,
779 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList*
780 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
781 UnoptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
782
783 CompilationJob::Status status = job->FinalizeJob(shared_info, isolate);
784 if (status == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
785 InstallUnoptimizedCode(compilation_info, shared_info, isolate);
786
787 MaybeHandle<CoverageInfo> coverage_info;
788 if (compilation_info->has_coverage_info()) {
789 SharedMutexGuardIfOffThread<IsolateT, base::kShared> mutex_guard(
790 isolate->shared_function_info_access(), isolate);
791 if (!shared_info->HasCoverageInfo(
792 isolate->GetMainThreadIsolateUnsafe())) {
793 coverage_info = compilation_info->coverage_info();
794 }
795 }
796
797 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list->emplace_back(
798 isolate, shared_info, coverage_info, job->time_taken_to_execute(),
799 job->time_taken_to_finalize());
800 }
801 DCHECK_IMPLIES(status == CompilationJob::RETRY_ON_MAIN_THREAD,
802 (std::is_same<IsolateT, LocalIsolate>::value));
803 return status;
804}
805
806std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob>
807ExecuteSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
808 ParseInfo* parse_info, FunctionLiteral* literal, Handle<Script> script,
809 AccountingAllocator* allocator,
810 std::vector<FunctionLiteral*>* eager_inner_literals,
811 LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
812#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
813 if (UseAsmWasm(literal, parse_info->flags().is_asm_wasm_broken())) {
814 std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> asm_job(
815 AsmJs::NewCompilationJob(parse_info, literal, allocator));
816 if (asm_job->ExecuteJob() == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
817 return asm_job;
818 }
819 // asm.js validation failed, fall through to standard unoptimized compile.
820 // Note: we rely on the fact that AsmJs jobs have done all validation in the
821 // PrepareJob and ExecuteJob phases and can't fail in FinalizeJob with
822 // with a validation error or another error that could be solve by falling
823 // through to standard unoptimized compile.
824 }
825#endif
826 std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> job(
827 interpreter::Interpreter::NewCompilationJob(
828 parse_info, literal, script, allocator, eager_inner_literals,
829 local_isolate));
830
831 if (job->ExecuteJob() != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
832 // Compilation failed, return null.
833 return std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob>();
834 }
835
836 return job;
837}
838
839template <typename IsolateT>
840bool IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
841 IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Script> script, ParseInfo* parse_info,
842 AccountingAllocator* allocator, IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope,
843 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList*
844 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list,
845 DeferredFinalizationJobDataList*
846 jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread) {
847 DeclarationScope::AllocateScopeInfos(parse_info, script, isolate);
848
849 std::vector<FunctionLiteral*> functions_to_compile;
850 functions_to_compile.push_back(parse_info->literal());
851
852 bool compilation_succeeded = true;
853 while (!functions_to_compile.empty()) {
854 FunctionLiteral* literal = functions_to_compile.back();
855 functions_to_compile.pop_back();
856 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = literal->shared_function_info();
857 // It's possible that compilation of an outer function overflowed the stack,
858 // so a literal we'd like to compile won't have its SFI yet. Skip compiling
859 // the inner function in that case.
860 if (shared_info.is_null()) continue;
861 if (shared_info->is_compiled()) continue;
862
863 std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> job =
864 ExecuteSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(parse_info, literal, script,
865 allocator, &functions_to_compile,
866 isolate->AsLocalIsolate());
867
868 if (!job) {
869 // Compilation failed presumably because of stack overflow, make sure
870 // the shared function info contains uncompiled data for the next
871 // compilation attempts.
872 if (!shared_info->HasUncompiledData()) {
873 SharedFunctionInfo::CreateAndSetUncompiledData(isolate, literal);
874 }
875 compilation_succeeded = false;
876 // Proceed finalizing other functions in case they don't have uncompiled
877 // data.
878 continue;
879 }
880
881 UpdateSharedFunctionFlagsAfterCompilation(literal);
882
883 auto finalization_status = FinalizeSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
884 job.get(), shared_info, isolate,
885 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
886
887 switch (finalization_status) {
888 case CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED:
889 if (literal == parse_info->literal()) {
890 // Ensure that the top level function is retained.
891 *is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
892 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
893 }
894 break;
895
896 case CompilationJob::FAILED:
897 compilation_succeeded = false;
898 // Proceed finalizing other functions in case they don't have uncompiled
899 // data.
900 continue;
901
902 case CompilationJob::RETRY_ON_MAIN_THREAD:
903 // This should not happen on the main thread.
904 DCHECK((!std::is_same<IsolateT, Isolate>::value));
905 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread);
906
907 // Clear the literal and ParseInfo to prevent further attempts to
908 // access them.
909 job->compilation_info()->ClearLiteral();
910 job->ClearParseInfo();
911 jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread->emplace_back(
912 isolate, shared_info, std::move(job));
913 break;
914 }
915 }
916
917 // Report any warnings generated during compilation.
918 if (parse_info->pending_error_handler()->has_pending_warnings()) {
919 parse_info->pending_error_handler()->PrepareWarnings(isolate);
920 }
921
922 return compilation_succeeded;
923}
924
925bool FinalizeDeferredUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
926 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> script,
927 DeferredFinalizationJobDataList* deferred_jobs,
928 PendingCompilationErrorHandler* pending_error_handler,
929 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList*
930 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
931 DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
932
933 if (deferred_jobs->empty()) return true;
934
935 // TODO(rmcilroy): Clear native context in debug once AsmJS generates doesn't
936 // rely on accessing native context during finalization.
937
938 // Finalize the deferred compilation jobs.
939 for (auto&& job : *deferred_jobs) {
940 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = job.function_handle();
941 if (FinalizeSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
942 job.job(), shared_info, isolate,
943 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) !=
944 CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
945 return false;
946 }
947 }
948
949 // Report any warnings generated during deferred finalization.
950 if (pending_error_handler->has_pending_warnings()) {
951 pending_error_handler->PrepareWarnings(isolate);
952 }
953
954 return true;
955}
956
957// A wrapper to access the optimized code cache slots on the feedback vector.
958class OptimizedCodeCache : public AllStatic {
959 public:
960 static V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeHandle<Code> Get(
961 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
962 BytecodeOffset osr_offset, CodeKind code_kind) {
963 DCHECK_IMPLIES(V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL, IsOSR(osr_offset));
964 if (!CodeKindIsStoredInOptimizedCodeCache(code_kind)) return {};
965 if (!function->has_feedback_vector()) return {};
966
967 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
968 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared();
969 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileGetFromOptimizedCodeMap);
970
971 Tagged<Code> code;
972 Tagged<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector = function->feedback_vector();
973 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
974 Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode(shared->GetBytecodeArray(isolate),
975 isolate);
976 interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode, osr_offset.ToInt());
977 // Bytecode may be different, so make sure we're at a valid OSR entry.
978 SBXCHECK(it.CurrentBytecodeIsValidOSREntry());
979 std::optional<Tagged<Code>> maybe_code =
980 feedback_vector->GetOptimizedOsrCode(isolate, it.GetSlotOperand(2));
981 if (maybe_code.has_value()) code = maybe_code.value();
982 } else {
983#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
984 UNREACHABLE();
985#else
986 feedback_vector->EvictOptimizedCodeMarkedForDeoptimization(
987 isolate, shared, "OptimizedCodeCache::Get");
988 code = feedback_vector->optimized_code(isolate);
989#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
990 }
991
992 // Normal tierup should never request a code-kind we already have. In case
993 // of OSR it can happen that we OSR from ignition to turbofan. This is
994 // explicitly allowed here by re-using any larger-kinded than requested
995 // code.
996 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!code.is_null() && code->kind() > code_kind,
997 IsOSR(osr_offset));
998 if (code.is_null() || code->kind() < code_kind) return {};
999
1000 DCHECK(!code->marked_for_deoptimization());
1001 DCHECK(shared->is_compiled());
1002 DCHECK(CodeKindIsStoredInOptimizedCodeCache(code->kind()));
1003 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsOSR(osr_offset), CodeKindCanOSR(code->kind()));
1004
1005 CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizedCodeCacheHit(isolate, function, osr_offset,
1006 code_kind);
1007 return handle(code, isolate);
1008 }
1009
1010 static void Insert(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSFunction> function,
1011 BytecodeOffset osr_offset, Tagged<Code> code,
1012 bool is_function_context_specializing) {
1013 DCHECK_IMPLIES(V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL, IsOSR(osr_offset));
1014 const CodeKind kind = code->kind();
1015 if (!CodeKindIsStoredInOptimizedCodeCache(kind)) return;
1016
1017 Tagged<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector = function->feedback_vector();
1018
1019 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1020 DCHECK(CodeKindCanOSR(kind));
1021 DCHECK(!is_function_context_specializing);
1022 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared();
1023 Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode(shared->GetBytecodeArray(isolate),
1024 isolate);
1025 interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode, osr_offset.ToInt());
1026 // Bytecode may be different, so make sure we're at a valid OSR entry.
1027 SBXCHECK(it.CurrentBytecodeIsValidOSREntry());
1028 feedback_vector->SetOptimizedOsrCode(isolate, it.GetSlotOperand(2), code);
1029 return;
1030 }
1031
1032#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1033 UNREACHABLE();
1034#else
1035 DCHECK(!IsOSR(osr_offset));
1036
1037 if (is_function_context_specializing) {
1038 // Function context specialization folds-in the function context, so no
1039 // sharing can occur. Make sure the optimized code cache is cleared.
1040 // Only do so if the specialized code's kind matches the cached code kind.
1041 if (feedback_vector->has_optimized_code() &&
1042 feedback_vector->optimized_code(isolate)->kind() == code->kind()) {
1043 feedback_vector->ClearOptimizedCode();
1044 }
1045 return;
1046 }
1047
1048 function->shared()->set_function_context_independent_compiled(true);
1049 feedback_vector->SetOptimizedCode(isolate, code);
1050#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1051 }
1052};
1053
1054// Runs PrepareJob in the proper compilation scopes. Handles will be allocated
1055// in a persistent handle scope that is detached and handed off to the
1056// {compilation_info} after PrepareJob.
1057bool PrepareJobWithHandleScope(OptimizedCompilationJob* job, Isolate* isolate,
1058 OptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
1059 ConcurrencyMode mode) {
1060 CompilationHandleScope compilation(isolate, compilation_info);
1061 CompilerTracer::TracePrepareJob(isolate, compilation_info, mode);
1062 compilation_info->ReopenAndCanonicalizeHandlesInNewScope(isolate);
1063 return job->PrepareJob(isolate) == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED;
1064}
1065
1066bool CompileTurbofan_NotConcurrent(Isolate* isolate,
1067 TurbofanCompilationJob* job) {
1068 OptimizedCompilationInfo* const compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
1069 DCHECK_EQ(compilation_info->code_kind(), CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
1070
1071 TimerEventScope<TimerEventRecompileSynchronous> timer(isolate);
1072 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeNonConcurrent);
1073 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1074 "V8.OptimizeNonConcurrent");
1075
1076 if (!PrepareJobWithHandleScope(job, isolate, compilation_info,
1077 ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous)) {
1078 CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
1079 job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
1080 job->finalize_in_ms());
1081 return false;
1082 }
1083
1084 if (job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats(),
1085 isolate->main_thread_local_isolate())) {
1086 CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
1087 job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
1088 job->finalize_in_ms());
1089 return false;
1090 }
1091
1092 if (job->FinalizeJob(isolate) != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
1093 CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
1094 job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
1095 job->finalize_in_ms());
1096 return false;
1097 }
1098
1099 // Success!
1100 job->RecordCompilationStats(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous, isolate);
1101 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1102 if (!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL || job->compilation_info()->is_osr()) {
1103 OptimizedCodeCache::Insert(
1104 isolate, *compilation_info->closure(), compilation_info->osr_offset(),
1105 *compilation_info->code(),
1106 compilation_info->function_context_specializing());
1107 }
1108 job->RecordFunctionCompilation(LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction, isolate);
1109 return true;
1110}
1111
1112bool CompileTurbofan_Concurrent(Isolate* isolate,
1113 std::unique_ptr<TurbofanCompilationJob> job) {
1114 OptimizedCompilationInfo* const compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
1115 DCHECK_EQ(compilation_info->code_kind(), CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
1116 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = compilation_info->closure();
1117
1118 if (!isolate->optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->IsQueueAvailable()) {
1119 if (v8_flags.trace_concurrent_recompilation) {
1120 PrintF(" ** Compilation queue full, will retry optimizing ");
1121 ShortPrint(*function);
1122 PrintF(" later.\n");
1123 }
1124 return false;
1125 }
1126
1127 if (isolate->heap()->HighMemoryPressure()) {
1128 if (v8_flags.trace_concurrent_recompilation) {
1129 PrintF(" ** High memory pressure, will retry optimizing ");
1130 ShortPrint(*function);
1131 PrintF(" later.\n");
1132 }
1133 return false;
1134 }
1135
1136 TimerEventScope<TimerEventRecompileSynchronous> timer(isolate);
1137 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeConcurrentPrepare);
1138 TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1139 "V8.OptimizeConcurrentPrepare", job->trace_id(),
1140 TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
1141
1142 if (!PrepareJobWithHandleScope(job.get(), isolate, compilation_info,
1143 ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent)) {
1144 return false;
1145 }
1146
1147 if (V8_LIKELY(!compilation_info->discard_result_for_testing())) {
1148 function->SetTieringInProgress(true, compilation_info->osr_offset());
1149 }
1150
1151 // The background recompile will own this job.
1152 isolate->optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->QueueForOptimization(job.release());
1153
1154 if (v8_flags.trace_concurrent_recompilation) {
1155 PrintF(" ** Queued ");
1156 ShortPrint(*function);
1157 PrintF(" for concurrent optimization.\n");
1158 }
1159
1160 DCHECK(compilation_info->shared_info()->HasBytecodeArray());
1161 return true;
1162}

1164enum class CompileResultBehavior {
1165 // Default behavior, i.e. install the result, insert into caches, etc.
1166 kDefault,
1167 // Used only for stress testing. The compilation result should be discarded.
1168 kDiscardForTesting,
1169};
1170
1171bool ShouldOptimize(CodeKind code_kind,
1172 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
1173 DCHECK(CodeKindIsOptimizedJSFunction(code_kind));
1174 switch (code_kind) {
1175 case CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS:
1176 return v8_flags.turbofan && shared->PassesFilter(v8_flags.turbo_filter);
1177 case CodeKind::MAGLEV:
1178 return maglev::IsMaglevEnabled() &&
1179 shared->PassesFilter(v8_flags.maglev_filter);
1180 default:
1181 UNREACHABLE();
1182 }
1183}
1184
1185MaybeHandle<Code> CompileTurbofan(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSFunction> function,
1186 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
1187 ConcurrencyMode mode,
1188 BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
1189 CompileResultBehavior result_behavior) {
1190 VMState<COMPILER> state(isolate);
1191 TimerEventScope<TimerEventOptimizeCode> optimize_code_timer(isolate);
1192 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeCode);
1193 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.OptimizeCode");
1194
1195 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1196 PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
1197 const compiler::IsScriptAvailable has_script =
1198 IsScript(shared->script()) ? compiler::IsScriptAvailable::kYes
1199 : compiler::IsScriptAvailable::kNo;
1200 // BUG(5946): This DCHECK is necessary to make certain that we won't
1201 // tolerate the lack of a script without bytecode.
1202 DCHECK_IMPLIES(has_script == compiler::IsScriptAvailable::kNo,
1203 shared->HasBytecodeArray());
1204 std::unique_ptr<TurbofanCompilationJob> job(
1205 compiler::NewCompilationJob(isolate, function, has_script, osr_offset));
1206
1207 if (result_behavior == CompileResultBehavior::kDiscardForTesting) {
1208 job->compilation_info()->set_discard_result_for_testing();
1209 }
1210
1211 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1212 isolate->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kTurboFanOsrCompileStarted);
1213 }
1214
1215 // Prepare the job and launch concurrent compilation, or compile now.
1216 if (IsConcurrent(mode)) {
1217 if (CompileTurbofan_Concurrent(isolate, std::move(job))) return {};
1218 } else {
1219 DCHECK(IsSynchronous(mode));
1220 if (CompileTurbofan_NotConcurrent(isolate, job.get())) {
1221 return job->compilation_info()->code();
1222 }
1223 }
1224
1225 if (isolate->has_exception()) isolate->clear_exception();
1226 return {};
1227}

1249MaybeHandle<Code> CompileMaglev(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSFunction> function,
1250 ConcurrencyMode mode, BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
1251 CompileResultBehavior result_behavior) {
1252#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1253 DCHECK(maglev::IsMaglevEnabled());
1254 CHECK(result_behavior == CompileResultBehavior::kDefault);
1255
1256 // TODO(v8:7700): Tracing, see CompileTurbofan.
1257
1258 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1259 PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
1260
1261 // TODO(v8:7700): See everything in CompileTurbofan_Concurrent.
1262 // - Tracing,
1263 // - timers,
1264 // - aborts on memory pressure,
1265 // ...
1266
1267 // Prepare the job.
1268 auto job = maglev::MaglevCompilationJob::New(isolate, function, osr_offset);
1269
1270 if (IsConcurrent(mode) &&
1271 !isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->is_enabled()) {
1272 mode = ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous;
1273 }
1274
1275 {
1276 TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(
1277 TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1278 IsSynchronous(mode) ? "V8.MaglevPrepare" : "V8.MaglevConcurrentPrepare",
1279 job->trace_id(), TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
1280 CompilerTracer::TraceStartMaglevCompile(isolate, function, job->is_osr(),
1281 mode);
1282 CompilationJob::Status status = job->PrepareJob(isolate);
1283 CHECK_EQ(status, CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED); // TODO(v8:7700): Use status.
1284 }
1285
1286 if (IsSynchronous(mode)) {
1287 CompilationJob::Status status =
1288 job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats(),
1289 isolate->main_thread_local_isolate());
1290 if (status == CompilationJob::FAILED) {
1291 return {};
1292 }
1293 CHECK_EQ(status, CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED);
1294
1295 Compiler::FinalizeMaglevCompilationJob(job.get(), isolate);
1296
1297 return job->code();
1298 }
1299
1300 DCHECK(IsConcurrent(mode));
1301
1302 // Enqueue it.
1303 isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->EnqueueJob(std::move(job));
1304
1305 // Remember that the function is currently being processed.
1306 function->SetTieringInProgress(true, osr_offset);
1307 function->SetInterruptBudget(isolate, BudgetModification::kRaise,
1308 CodeKind::MAGLEV);
1309
1310 return {};
1311#else // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1312 UNREACHABLE();
1313#endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1314}
1315
1316MaybeHandle<Code> GetOrCompileOptimized(
1317 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function, ConcurrencyMode mode,
1318 CodeKind code_kind, BytecodeOffset osr_offset = BytecodeOffset::None(),
1319 CompileResultBehavior result_behavior = CompileResultBehavior::kDefault) {
1320 DCHECK(CodeKindIsOptimizedJSFunction(code_kind));
1321
1322 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(), isolate);
1323
1324 // Clear the optimization marker on the function so that we don't try to
1325 // re-optimize.
1326 if (!IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1327 function->ResetTieringRequests(isolate);
1328 // Always reset the OSR urgency to ensure we reset it on function entry.
1329 function->feedback_vector()->reset_osr_urgency();
1330 int invocation_count =
1331 function->feedback_vector()->invocation_count(kRelaxedLoad);
1332 if (!(V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.testing_d8_test_runner ||
1333 v8_flags.allow_natives_syntax) &&
1334 ManualOptimizationTable::IsMarkedForManualOptimization(isolate,
1335 *function)) &&
1336 invocation_count < v8_flags.minimum_invocations_before_optimization) {
1337 function->feedback_vector()->set_invocation_count(invocation_count + 1,
1338 kRelaxedStore);
1339 return {};
1340 }
1341 }
1342
1343 // TODO(v8:7700): Distinguish between Maglev and Turbofan.
1344 if (shared->optimization_disabled() &&
1345 shared->disabled_optimization_reason() == BailoutReason::kNeverOptimize) {
1346 return {};
1347 }
1348
1349 // Do not optimize when debugger needs to hook into every call.
1350 if (isolate->debug()->needs_check_on_function_call()) {
1351 // Reset the OSR urgency to avoid triggering this compilation request on
1352 // every iteration and thereby skipping other interrupts.
1353 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1354 function->feedback_vector()->reset_osr_urgency();
1355 }
1356 return {};
1357 }
1358
1359 // Do not optimize if we need to be able to set break points.
1360 if (shared->HasBreakInfo(isolate)) return {};
1361
1362 // Do not optimize if optimization is disabled or function doesn't pass
1363 // turbo_filter.
1364 if (!ShouldOptimize(code_kind, shared)) return {};
1365
1366 if (!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL || IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1367 Handle<Code> cached_code;
1368 if (OptimizedCodeCache::Get(isolate, function, osr_offset, code_kind)
1369 .ToHandle(&cached_code)) {
1370 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1371 if (!function->osr_tiering_in_progress()) {
1372 function->feedback_vector()->reset_osr_urgency();
1373 }
1374 } else {
1375 DCHECK_LE(cached_code->kind(), code_kind);
1376 }
1377 return cached_code;
1378 }
1379
1380 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1381 // One OSR job per function at a time.
1382 if (function->osr_tiering_in_progress()) {
1383 return {};
1384 }
1385 function->feedback_vector()->reset_osr_urgency();
1386 }
1387 }
1388
1389 DCHECK(shared->is_compiled());
1390
1391 if (code_kind == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
1392 return CompileTurbofan(isolate, indirect_handle(function, isolate), shared,
1393 mode, osr_offset, result_behavior);
1394 } else {
1395 DCHECK_EQ(code_kind, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
1396 return CompileMaglev(isolate, indirect_handle(function, isolate), mode,
1397 osr_offset, result_behavior);
1398 }
1399}

1401// When --stress-concurrent-inlining is enabled, spawn concurrent jobs in
1402// addition to non-concurrent compiles to increase coverage in mjsunit tests
1403// (where most interesting compiles are non-concurrent). The result of the
1404// compilation is thrown out.
1405void SpawnDuplicateConcurrentJobForStressTesting(
1406 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function, ConcurrencyMode mode,
1407 CodeKind code_kind) {
1408 // TODO(v8:7700): Support Maglev.
1409 if (code_kind == CodeKind::MAGLEV) return;
1410
1411 if (function->ActiveTierIsTurbofan(isolate)) return;
1412
1413 DCHECK(v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining &&
1414 isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled() && IsSynchronous(mode) &&
1415 isolate->node_observer() == nullptr);
1416 CompileResultBehavior result_behavior =
1417 v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining_attach_code
1418 ? CompileResultBehavior::kDefault
1419 : CompileResultBehavior::kDiscardForTesting;
1420 USE(GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent,
1421 code_kind, BytecodeOffset::None(),
1422 result_behavior));
1423}

1425bool FailAndClearException(Isolate* isolate) {
1426 isolate->clear_internal_exception();
1427 return false;
1428}
1429
1430template <typename IsolateT>
1431bool PrepareException(IsolateT* isolate, ParseInfo* parse_info) {
1432 if (parse_info->pending_error_handler()->has_pending_error()) {
1433 parse_info->pending_error_handler()->PrepareErrors(
1434 isolate, parse_info->ast_value_factory());
1435 }
1436 return false;
1437}
1438
1439bool FailWithPreparedException(
1440 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1441 const PendingCompilationErrorHandler* pending_error_handler,
1442 Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag = Compiler::KEEP_EXCEPTION) {
1443 if (flag == Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION) {
1444 return FailAndClearException(isolate);
1445 }
1446
1447 if (!isolate->has_exception()) {
1448 if (pending_error_handler->has_pending_error()) {
1449 pending_error_handler->ReportErrors(isolate, script);
1450 } else {
1451 isolate->StackOverflow();
1452 }
1453 }
1454 return false;
1455}
1456
1457bool FailWithException(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1458 ParseInfo* parse_info,
1459 Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag) {
1460 PrepareException(isolate, parse_info);
1461 return FailWithPreparedException(isolate, script,
1462 parse_info->pending_error_handler(), flag);
1463}
1464
1465void FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(
1466 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1467 const UnoptimizedCompileFlags& flags,
1468 const UnoptimizedCompileState* compile_state,
1469 const FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList&
1470 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1471 if (compile_state->pending_error_handler()->has_pending_warnings()) {
1472 compile_state->pending_error_handler()->ReportWarnings(isolate, script);
1473 }
1474
1475 bool need_source_positions =
1476 v8_flags.stress_lazy_source_positions ||
1477 (!flags.collect_source_positions() && isolate->NeedsSourcePositions());
1478
1479 for (const auto& finalize_data : finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1480 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = finalize_data.function_handle();
1481 // It's unlikely, but possible, that the bytecode was flushed between being
1482 // allocated and now, so guard against that case, and against it being
1483 // flushed in the middle of this loop.
1484 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(*shared_info, isolate);
1485 if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) continue;
1486
1487 if (need_source_positions) {
1488 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, shared_info);
1489 }
1490 LogEventListener::CodeTag log_tag;
1491 if (shared_info->is_toplevel()) {
1492 log_tag = flags.is_eval() ? LogEventListener::CodeTag::kEval
1493 : LogEventListener::CodeTag::kScript;
1494 } else {
1495 log_tag = LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction;
1496 }
1497 log_tag = V8FileLogger::ToNativeByScript(log_tag, *script);
1498 if (isolate->interpreted_frames_native_stack() &&
1499 isolate->logger()->is_listening_to_code_events()) {
1500 Compiler::InstallInterpreterTrampolineCopy(isolate, shared_info, log_tag);
1501 }
1502 DirectHandle<CoverageInfo> coverage_info;
1503 if (finalize_data.coverage_info().ToHandle(&coverage_info)) {
1504 isolate->debug()->InstallCoverageInfo(shared_info, coverage_info);
1505 }
1506
1507 LogUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, shared_info, log_tag,
1508 finalize_data.time_taken_to_execute(),
1509 finalize_data.time_taken_to_finalize());
1510 }
1511}
1512
1513void FinalizeUnoptimizedScriptCompilation(
1514 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1515 const UnoptimizedCompileFlags& flags,
1516 const UnoptimizedCompileState* compile_state,
1517 const FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList&
1518 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1519 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, script, flags, compile_state,
1520 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
1521
1522 script->set_compilation_state(Script::CompilationState::kCompiled);
1523 DCHECK_IMPLIES(isolate->NeedsSourcePositions(), script->has_line_ends());
1524}

1526void CompileAllWithBaseline(Isolate* isolate,
1527 const FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList&
1528 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1529 for (const auto& finalize_data : finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1530 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = finalize_data.function_handle();
1531 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(*shared_info, isolate);
1532 if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) continue;
1533 if (!CanCompileWithBaseline(isolate, *shared_info)) continue;
1534 Compiler::CompileSharedWithBaseline(
1535 isolate, shared_info, Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION, &is_compiled_scope);
1536 }
1537}

1539// Create shared function info for top level and shared function infos array for
1540// inner functions.
1541template <typename IsolateT>
1542Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> CreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(
1543 ParseInfo* parse_info, Handle<Script> script, IsolateT* isolate) {
1544 EnsureInfosArrayOnScript(script, parse_info, isolate);
1545 DCHECK_EQ(kNoSourcePosition,
1546 parse_info->literal()->function_token_position());
1547 return isolate->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForLiteral(
1548 parse_info->literal(), script, true);
1549}
1550
1551Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> GetOrCreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(
1552 ParseInfo* parse_info, Handle<Script> script, Isolate* isolate,
1553 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
1554 EnsureInfosArrayOnScript(script, parse_info, isolate);
1555 MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_shared =
1556 Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(script, isolate, parse_info->literal());
1557 if (Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared; maybe_shared.ToHandle(&shared)) {
1558 DCHECK_EQ(shared->function_literal_id(),
1559 parse_info->literal()->function_literal_id());
1560 *is_compiled_scope = shared->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
1561 return shared;
1562 }
1563 return CreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(parse_info, script, isolate);
1564}
1565
1566MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> CompileToplevel(
1567 ParseInfo* parse_info, Handle<Script> script,
1568 MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info, Isolate* isolate,
1569 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
1570 TimerEventScope<TimerEventCompileCode> top_level_timer(isolate);
1571 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.CompileCode");
1572 DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
1573
1574 PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
1575 DCHECK(!isolate->native_context().is_null());
1576 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, parse_info->flags().is_eval()
1577 ? RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileEval
1578 : RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileScript);
1579 VMState<BYTECODE_COMPILER> state(isolate);
1580 if (parse_info->literal() == nullptr &&
1581 !parsing::ParseProgram(parse_info, script, maybe_outer_scope_info,
1582 isolate, parsing::ReportStatisticsMode::kYes)) {
1583 FailWithException(isolate, script, parse_info,
1584 Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag::KEEP_EXCEPTION);
1585 return MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>();
1586 }
1587 // Measure how long it takes to do the compilation; only take the
1588 // rest of the function into account to avoid overlap with the
1589 // parsing statistics.
1590 NestedTimedHistogram* rate = parse_info->flags().is_eval()
1591 ? isolate->counters()->compile_eval()
1592 : isolate->counters()->compile();
1593 NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(rate);
1594 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1595 parse_info->flags().is_eval() ? "V8.CompileEval" : "V8.Compile");
1596
1597 // Create the SharedFunctionInfo and add it to the script's list.
1598 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1599 GetOrCreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(parse_info, script, isolate,
1600 is_compiled_scope);
1601
1602 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList
1603 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list;
1604
1605 // Prepare and execute compilation of the outer-most function.
1606 if (!IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
1607 isolate, script, parse_info, isolate->allocator(), is_compiled_scope,
1608 &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list, nullptr)) {
1609 FailWithException(isolate, script, parse_info,
1610 Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag::KEEP_EXCEPTION);
1611 return MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>();
1612 }
1613
1614 // Character stream shouldn't be used again.
1615 parse_info->ResetCharacterStream();
1616
1617 FinalizeUnoptimizedScriptCompilation(
1618 isolate, script, parse_info->flags(), parse_info->state(),
1619 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
1620
1621 if (v8_flags.always_sparkplug) {
1622 CompileAllWithBaseline(isolate, finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
1623 }
1624
1625 return shared_info;
1626}

1630 if (parse_info->flags().is_toplevel()) {
1631 if (parse_info->flags().is_eval()) {
1632 return RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileEval;
1633 }
1634 return RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileScript;
1635 }
1636 return RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileFunction;
1637}

1733void SetScriptFieldsFromDetails(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<Script> script,
1734 const ScriptDetails& script_details,
1735 DisallowGarbageCollection* no_gc) {
1736 Handle<Object> script_name;
1737 if (script_details.name_obj.ToHandle(&script_name)) {
1738 script->set_name(*script_name);
1739 script->set_line_offset(script_details.line_offset);
1740 script->set_column_offset(script_details.column_offset);
1741 }
1742 // The API can provide a source map URL, but a source map URL could also have
1743 // been inferred by the parser from a magic comment. The API source map URL
1744 // takes precedence (as long as it is a non-empty string).
1745 Handle<Object> source_map_url;
1746 if (script_details.source_map_url.ToHandle(&source_map_url) &&
1747 IsString(*source_map_url) &&
1748 Cast<String>(*source_map_url)->length() > 0) {
1749 script->set_source_mapping_url(*source_map_url);
1750 }
1751 Handle<Object> host_defined_options;
1752 if (script_details.host_defined_options.ToHandle(&host_defined_options)) {
1753 // TODO(cbruni, chromium:1244145): Remove once migrated to the context.
1754 if (IsFixedArray(*host_defined_options)) {
1755 script->set_host_defined_options(Cast<FixedArray>(*host_defined_options));
1756 }
1757 }

1762#ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
1763
1764// A class which traverses the object graph for a newly compiled Script and
1765// ensures that it contains pointers to Scripts, ScopeInfos and
1766// SharedFunctionInfos only at the expected locations. Any failure in this
1767// visitor indicates a case that is probably not handled correctly in
1768// BackgroundMergeTask.
1769class MergeAssumptionChecker final : public ObjectVisitor {
1770 public:
1771 explicit MergeAssumptionChecker(LocalIsolate* isolate)
1772 : isolate_(isolate), cage_base_(isolate->cage_base()) {}
1773
1774 void IterateObjects(Tagged<HeapObject> start) {
1775 QueueVisit(start, kNormalObject);
1776 while (to_visit_.size() > 0) {
1777 std::pair<Tagged<HeapObject>, ObjectKind> pair = to_visit_.top();
1778 to_visit_.pop();
1779 Tagged<HeapObject> current = pair.first;
1780 // The Script's infos list and the constant pools for all
1781 // BytecodeArrays are expected to contain pointers to SharedFunctionInfos.
1782 // However, the type of those objects (FixedArray or WeakFixedArray)
1783 // doesn't have enough information to indicate their usage, so we enqueue
1784 // those objects here rather than during VisitPointers.
1785 if (IsScript(current)) {
1786 Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(current);
1787 Tagged<HeapObject> infos = script->infos();
1788 QueueVisit(infos, kScriptInfosList);
1789 // Avoid visiting eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments. This field
1790 // points to data outside the new Script, and doesn't need to be merged.
1791 Tagged<HeapObject> eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments;
1792 if (script->eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments()
1793 .GetHeapObjectIfStrong(
1794 &eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments)) {
1795 visited_.insert(eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments);
1796 }
1797 } else if (IsBytecodeArray(current)) {
1798 Tagged<HeapObject> constants =
1799 Cast<BytecodeArray>(current)->constant_pool();
1800 QueueVisit(constants, kConstantPool);
1801 }
1802 current_object_kind_ = pair.second;
1803 i::VisitObjectBody(isolate_, current, this);
1804 QueueVisit(current->map(), kNormalObject);
1805 }
1806 }
1807
1808 // ObjectVisitor implementation:
1809 void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot start,
1810 ObjectSlot end) override {
1811 MaybeObjectSlot maybe_start(start);
1812 MaybeObjectSlot maybe_end(end);
1813 VisitPointers(host, maybe_start, maybe_end);
1814 }
1815 void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, MaybeObjectSlot start,
1816 MaybeObjectSlot end) override {
1817 for (MaybeObjectSlot current = start; current != end; ++current) {
1818 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_obj = current.load(cage_base_);
1819 Tagged<HeapObject> obj;
1820 bool is_weak = maybe_obj.IsWeak();
1821 if (maybe_obj.GetHeapObject(&obj)) {
1822 if (IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj)) {
1823 CHECK((current_object_kind_ == kConstantPool && !is_weak) ||
1824 (current_object_kind_ == kScriptInfosList && is_weak) ||
1825 (IsScript(host) &&
1826 current.address() ==
1827 host.address() +
1828 Script::kEvalFromSharedOrWrappedArgumentsOffset));
1829 } else if (IsScopeInfo(obj)) {
1830 CHECK((current_object_kind_ == kConstantPool && !is_weak) ||
1831 (current_object_kind_ == kNormalObject && !is_weak) ||
1832 (current_object_kind_ == kScriptInfosList && is_weak));
1833 } else if (IsScript(obj)) {
1834 CHECK(IsSharedFunctionInfo(host) &&
1835 current == MaybeObjectSlot(host.address() +
1836 SharedFunctionInfo::kScriptOffset));
1837 } else if (IsFixedArray(obj) && current_object_kind_ == kConstantPool) {
1838 // Constant pools can contain nested fixed arrays, which in turn can
1839 // point to SFIs.
1840 QueueVisit(obj, kConstantPool);
1841 }
1842
1843 QueueVisit(obj, kNormalObject);
1844 }
1845 }
1846 }
1847
1848 // The object graph for a newly compiled Script shouldn't yet contain any
1849 // Code. If any of these functions are called, then that would indicate that
1850 // the graph was not disjoint from the rest of the heap as expected.
1851 void VisitInstructionStreamPointer(Tagged<Code> host,
1852 InstructionStreamSlot slot) override {
1853 UNREACHABLE();
1854 }
1855 void VisitCodeTarget(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
1856 RelocInfo* rinfo) override {
1857 UNREACHABLE();
1858 }
1859 void VisitEmbeddedPointer(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
1860 RelocInfo* rinfo) override {
1861 UNREACHABLE();
1862 }
1863
1864 private:
1865 enum ObjectKind {
1866 kNormalObject,
1867 kConstantPool,
1868 kScriptInfosList,
1869 };
1870
1871 // If the object hasn't yet been added to the worklist, add it. Subsequent
1872 // calls with the same object have no effect, even if kind is different.
1873 void QueueVisit(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, ObjectKind kind) {
1874 if (visited_.insert(obj).second) {
1875 to_visit_.push(std::make_pair(obj, kind));
1876 }
1877 }
1878
1879 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc_;
1880
1881 LocalIsolate* isolate_;
1882 PtrComprCageBase cage_base_;
1883 std::stack<std::pair<Tagged<HeapObject>, ObjectKind>> to_visit_;
1884
1885 // Objects that are either in to_visit_ or done being visited. It is safe to
1886 // use HeapObject directly here because GC is disallowed while running this
1887 // visitor.
1888 std::unordered_set<Tagged<HeapObject>, Object::Hasher> visited_;
1889
1890 ObjectKind current_object_kind_ = kNormalObject;
1891};

1893#endif // ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS

1918void BackgroundCompileTask::Run(
1919 LocalIsolate* isolate, ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState* reusable_state) {
1920 TimedHistogramScope timer(
1921 timer_, nullptr,
1922 compilation_details_
1923 ? &compilation_details_->background_time_in_microseconds
1924 : nullptr);
1925
1926 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1927 "BackgroundCompileTask::Run");
1928 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileCompileTask,
1929 RuntimeCallStats::CounterMode::kThreadSpecific);
1930
1931 bool toplevel_script_compilation = flags_.is_toplevel();
1932
1933 ParseInfo info(isolate, flags_, &compile_state_, reusable_state,
1934 GetCurrentStackPosition() - stack_size_ * KB);
1935 info.set_character_stream(std::move(character_stream_));
1936 info.SetCompileHintCallbackAndData(compile_hint_callback_,
1937 compile_hint_callback_data_);
1938 if (is_streaming_compilation()) info.set_is_streaming_compilation();
1939
1940 if (toplevel_script_compilation) {
1941 DCHECK_NULL(persistent_handles_);
1942 DCHECK(input_shared_info_.is_null());
1943
1944 // We don't have the script source, origin, or details yet, so use default
1945 // values for them. These will be fixed up during the main-thread merge.
1946 Handle<Script> script = info.CreateScript(
1947 isolate, isolate->factory()->empty_string(), kNullMaybeHandle,
1948 ScriptOriginOptions(false, false, false, info.flags().is_module()));
1949 script_ = isolate->heap()->NewPersistentHandle(script);
1950 } else {
1951 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(persistent_handles_);
1952 isolate->heap()->AttachPersistentHandles(std::move(persistent_handles_));
1953 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1954 input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked();
1955 script_ = isolate->heap()->NewPersistentHandle(
1956 Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()));
1957 info.CheckFlagsForFunctionFromScript(*script_);
1958
1959 {
1960 SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded access_guard(isolate);
1961 info.set_function_name(info.ast_value_factory()->GetString(
1962 shared_info->Name(), access_guard));
1963 }
1964
1965 // Get preparsed scope data from the function literal.
1966 if (shared_info->HasUncompiledDataWithPreparseData()) {
1967 info.set_consumed_preparse_data(ConsumedPreparseData::For(
1968 isolate,
1969 handle(shared_info->uncompiled_data_with_preparse_data(isolate)
1970 ->preparse_data(isolate),
1971 isolate)));
1972 }
1973 }
1974
1975 // Update the character stream's runtime call stats.
1976 info.character_stream()->set_runtime_call_stats(info.runtime_call_stats());
1977
1978 Parser parser(isolate, &info);
1979 if (flags().is_toplevel()) {
1980 parser.InitializeEmptyScopeChain(&info);
1981 } else {
1982 // TODO(leszeks): Consider keeping Scope zones alive between compile tasks
1983 // and passing the Scope for the FunctionLiteral through here directly
1984 // without copying/deserializing.
1985 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1986 input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked();
1987 MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info;
1988 if (shared_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
1989 maybe_outer_scope_info =
1990 direct_handle(shared_info->GetOuterScopeInfo(), isolate);
1991 }
1992 parser.DeserializeScopeChain(
1993 isolate, &info, maybe_outer_scope_info,
1994 Scope::DeserializationMode::kIncludingVariables);
1995 }
1996
1997 parser.ParseOnBackground(isolate, &info, script_, start_position_,
1998 end_position_, function_literal_id_);
1999 parser.UpdateStatistics(script_, &use_counts_, &total_preparse_skipped_);
2000
2001 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2002 "V8.CompileCodeBackground");
2003 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterIdForCompile(&info),
2004 RuntimeCallStats::CounterMode::kThreadSpecific);
2005
2006 MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
2007 if (info.literal() != nullptr) {
2008 if (toplevel_script_compilation) {
2009 CreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(&info, script_, isolate);
2010 } else {
2011 // Clone into a placeholder SFI for storing the results.
2012 info.literal()->set_shared_function_info(
2013 isolate->factory()->CloneSharedFunctionInfo(
2014 input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked()));
2015 }
2016
2017 if (IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2018 isolate, script_, &info, reusable_state->allocator(),
2019 &is_compiled_scope_, &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_,
2020 &jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread_)) {
2021 maybe_result = info.literal()->shared_function_info();
2022 }
2023 }
2024
2025 if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
2026 PrepareException(isolate, &info);
2027 } else if (v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts) {
2028#ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
2029 MergeAssumptionChecker checker(isolate);
2030 checker.IterateObjects(*maybe_result.ToHandleChecked());
2031#endif
2032 }
2033
2034 outer_function_sfi_ = isolate->heap()->NewPersistentMaybeHandle(maybe_result);
2035 DCHECK(isolate->heap()->ContainsPersistentHandle(script_.location()));
2036 persistent_handles_ = isolate->heap()->DetachPersistentHandles();
2037}

2039// A class which traverses the constant pools of newly compiled
2040// SharedFunctionInfos and updates any pointers which need updating.
2041class ConstantPoolPointerForwarder {
2042 public:
2043 explicit ConstantPoolPointerForwarder(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
2044 LocalHeap* local_heap,
2045 DirectHandle<Script> old_script)
2046 : cage_base_(cage_base),
2047 local_heap_(local_heap),
2048 old_script_(old_script) {}
2049
2050 void AddBytecodeArray(Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array) {
2051 CHECK(IsBytecodeArray(bytecode_array));
2052 bytecode_arrays_to_update_.emplace_back(bytecode_array, local_heap_);
2053 }
2054
2055 void RecordScopeInfos(Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_info) {
2056 RecordScopeInfos(maybe_old_info.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2057 }
2058
2059 // Record all scope infos relevant for a shared function info or scope info
2060 // (recorded for eval).
2061 void RecordScopeInfos(Tagged<HeapObject> info) {
2062 Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info;
2063 if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(info)) {
2064 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> old_sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(info);
2065 // Also record context-having own scope infos for SFIs.
2066 if (!old_sfi->scope_info()->IsEmpty() &&
2067 old_sfi->scope_info()->HasContext()) {
2068 scope_info = old_sfi->scope_info();
2069 } else if (old_sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2070 scope_info = old_sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo();
2071 } else {
2072 return;
2073 }
2074 } else {
2075 scope_info = Cast<ScopeInfo>(info);
2076 }
2077
2078 while (true) {
2079 auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(scope_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2080 if (it != scope_infos_to_update_.end()) {
2081 // Once we find an already recorded scope info, it need to match the one
2082 // on the chain.
2083 if (V8_UNLIKELY(*it->second != scope_info)) {
2084 info->Print();
2085 (*it->second)->Print();
2086 scope_info->Print();
2087 UNREACHABLE();
2088 }
2089 return;
2090 }
2091 scope_infos_to_update_[scope_info->UniqueIdInScript()] =
2092 handle(scope_info, local_heap_);
2093 if (!scope_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) break;
2094 scope_info = scope_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2095 }
2096 }
2097
2098 // Runs the update after the setup functions above specified the work to do.
2099 void IterateAndForwardPointers() {
2100 DCHECK(HasAnythingToForward());
2101 for (DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> entry : bytecode_arrays_to_update_) {
2102 local_heap_->Safepoint();
2103 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2104 IterateConstantPool(entry->constant_pool());
2105 }
2106 }
2107
2108 void set_has_shared_function_info_to_forward() {
2109 has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ = true;
2110 }
2111
2112 bool HasAnythingToForward() const {
2113 return has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ ||
2114 !scope_infos_to_update_.empty();
2115 }
2116
2117 // Find an own scope info for the sfi based on the UniqueIdInScript that the
2118 // own scope info would have. This works even if the SFI doesn't yet have a
2119 // scope info attached by computing UniqueIdInScript from the SFI position.
2120 //
2121 // This should only directly be used for SFIs that already existed on the
2122 // script. Their outer scope info will already be correct.
2123 bool InstallOwnScopeInfo(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi) {
2124 auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(sfi->UniqueIdInScript());
2125 if (it == scope_infos_to_update_.end()) return false;
2126 sfi->SetScopeInfo(*it->second);
2127 return true;
2128 }
2129
2130 // Either replace the own scope info of the sfi, or the first outer scope info
2131 // that was recorded.
2132 //
2133 // This has to be used for all newly created SFIs since their outer scope info
2134 // also may need to be reattached.
2135 void UpdateScopeInfo(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi) {
2136 if (InstallOwnScopeInfo(sfi)) return;
2137 if (!sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) return;
2138
2139 Tagged<ScopeInfo> parent =
2140 sfi->scope_info()->IsEmpty() ? Tagged<ScopeInfo>() : sfi->scope_info();
2141 Tagged<ScopeInfo> outer_info = sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo();
2142
2143 auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(outer_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2144 while (it == scope_infos_to_update_.end()) {
2145 if (!outer_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) return;
2146 parent = outer_info;
2147 outer_info = outer_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2148 it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(outer_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2149 }
2150 if (outer_info == *it->second) return;
2151
2152 VerifyScopeInfo(outer_info, *it->second);
2153
2154 if (parent.is_null()) {
2155 sfi->set_raw_outer_scope_info_or_feedback_metadata(*it->second);
2156 } else {
2157 parent->set_outer_scope_info(*it->second);
2158 }
2159 }
2160
2161 private:
2162 void VerifyScopeInfo(Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info,
2163 Tagged<ScopeInfo> replacement) {
2164 CHECK_EQ(replacement->EndPosition(), scope_info->EndPosition());
2165 CHECK_EQ(replacement->scope_type(), scope_info->scope_type());
2166 CHECK_EQ(replacement->ContextLength(), scope_info->ContextLength());
2167 }
2168 template <typename TArray>
2169 void IterateConstantPoolEntry(Tagged<TArray> constant_pool, int i) {
2170 Tagged<Object> obj = constant_pool->get(i);
2171 if (IsSmi(obj)) return;
2172 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(obj);
2173 if (IsFixedArray(heap_obj, cage_base_)) {
2174 // Constant pools can have nested fixed arrays, but such relationships
2175 // are acyclic and never more than a few layers deep, so recursion is
2176 // fine here.
2177 IterateConstantPoolNestedArray(Cast<FixedArray>(heap_obj));
2178 } else if (has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ &&
2179 IsSharedFunctionInfo(heap_obj, cage_base_)) {
2180 VisitSharedFunctionInfo(constant_pool, i,
2181 Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(heap_obj));
2182 } else if (!scope_infos_to_update_.empty() &&
2183 IsScopeInfo(heap_obj, cage_base_)) {
2184 VisitScopeInfo(constant_pool, i, Cast<ScopeInfo>(heap_obj));
2185 }
2186 }
2187
2188 template <typename TArray>
2189 void VisitSharedFunctionInfo(Tagged<TArray> constant_pool, int i,
2190 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi) {
2191 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_sfi =
2192 old_script_->infos()->get(sfi->function_literal_id());
2193 if (maybe_old_sfi.IsWeak()) {
2194 constant_pool->set(
2195 i, Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_old_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak()));
2196 }
2197 }
2198
2199 template <typename TArray>
2200 void VisitScopeInfo(Tagged<TArray> constant_pool, int i,
2201 Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info) {
2202 auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(scope_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2203 // Try to replace the scope info itself with an already existing version.
2204 if (it != scope_infos_to_update_.end()) {
2205 if (scope_info != *it->second) {
2206 VerifyScopeInfo(scope_info, *it->second);
2207 constant_pool->set(i, *it->second);
2208 }
2209 } else if (scope_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2210 // If we didn't find a match, but we have an outer scope info, try to
2211 // replace the outer scope info with an already existing outer scope
2212 // info. We only need to look at the direct outer scope info since we'll
2213 // process all scope infos that are created by this compilation task.
2214 Tagged<ScopeInfo> outer = scope_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2215 it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(outer->UniqueIdInScript());
2216 if (it != scope_infos_to_update_.end() && outer != *it->second) {
2217 VerifyScopeInfo(outer, *it->second);
2218 scope_info->set_outer_scope_info(*it->second);
2219 }
2220 }
2221 }
2222
2223 void IterateConstantPool(Tagged<TrustedFixedArray> constant_pool) {
2224 for (int i = 0, length = constant_pool->length(); i < length; ++i) {
2225 IterateConstantPoolEntry(constant_pool, i);
2226 }
2227 }
2228
2229 void IterateConstantPoolNestedArray(Tagged<FixedArray> nested_array) {
2230 for (int i = 0, length = nested_array->length(); i < length; ++i) {
2231 IterateConstantPoolEntry(nested_array, i);
2232 }
2233 }
2234
2235 PtrComprCageBase cage_base_;
2236 LocalHeap* local_heap_;
2237 DirectHandle<Script> old_script_;
2238 std::vector<IndirectHandle<BytecodeArray>> bytecode_arrays_to_update_;
2239
2240 // Indicates whether we have any shared function info to forward.
2241 bool has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ = false;
2242 std::unordered_map<int, IndirectHandle<ScopeInfo>> scope_infos_to_update_;
2243};
2244
2245void BackgroundMergeTask::SetUpOnMainThread(Isolate* isolate,
2246 Handle<String> source_text,
2247 const ScriptDetails& script_details,
2248 LanguageMode language_mode) {
2249 DCHECK_EQ(state_, kNotStarted);
2250
2251 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2252
2253 CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
2254 isolate->compilation_cache()->LookupScript(source_text, script_details,
2255 language_mode);
2256 DirectHandle<Script> script;
2257 if (!lookup_result.script().ToHandle(&script)) {
2258 state_ = kDone;
2259 return;
2260 }
2261
2262 if (lookup_result.is_compiled_scope().is_compiled()) {
2263 // There already exists a compiled top-level SFI, so the main thread will
2264 // discard the background serialization results and use the top-level SFI
2265 // from the cache, assuming the top-level SFI is still compiled by then.
2266 // Thus, there is no need to keep the Script pointer for background merging.
2267 // Do nothing in this case.
2268 state_ = kDone;
2269 } else {
2270 DCHECK(lookup_result.toplevel_sfi().is_null());
2271 // A background merge is required.
2272 SetUpOnMainThread(isolate, script);
2273 }
2274}
