2276namespace {
2277void VerifyCodeMerge(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> script) {
2278 // Check that:
2279 // * There aren't any duplicate scope info. Every scope/context should
2280 // correspond to at most one scope info.
2281 // * All published SFIs refer to the old script (i.e. we chose new vs old
2282 // correctly, and updated new SFIs where needed).
2283 // * All constant pool SFI entries point to an SFI referring to the old
2284 // script (i.e. references were updated correctly).
2285 std::unordered_map<int, Tagged<ScopeInfo>> scope_infos;
2286 for (int i = 0; i < script->infos()->length(); i++) {
2287 Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info;
2288 if (!script->infos()->get(i).IsWeak()) continue;
2289 Tagged<HeapObject> info = script->infos()->get(i).GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak();
2290 if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(info)) {
2291 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(info);
2292 CHECK_EQ(sfi->script(), *script);
2293
2294 if (sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2295 Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode = sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate);
2296 Tagged<TrustedFixedArray> constant_pool = bytecode->constant_pool();
2297 for (int i = 0; i < constant_pool->length(); ++i) {
2298 Tagged<Object> entry = constant_pool->get(i);
2299 if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(entry)) {
2300 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> inner_sfi =
2301 Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(entry);
2302 int id = inner_sfi->function_literal_id();
2303 CHECK_EQ(MakeWeak(inner_sfi), script->infos()->get(id));
2304 CHECK_EQ(inner_sfi->script(), *script);
2305 }
2306 }
2307 }
2308
2309 if (!sfi->scope_info()->IsEmpty()) {
2310 scope_info = sfi->scope_info();
2311 } else if (sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2312 scope_info = sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo();
2313 } else {
2314 continue;
2315 }
2316 } else {
2317 scope_info = Cast<ScopeInfo>(info);
2318 }
2319 while (true) {
2320 auto it = scope_infos.find(scope_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2321 if (it != scope_infos.end()) {
2322 if (*it->second != scope_info) {
2323 isolate->PushParamsAndDie(reinterpret_cast<void*>(it->second->ptr()),
2324 reinterpret_cast<void*>(scope_info.ptr()));
2325 UNREACHABLE();
2326 }
2327 break;
2328 }
2329 scope_infos[scope_info->UniqueIdInScript()] = scope_info;
2330 if (!scope_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) break;
2331 scope_info = scope_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2332 }
2333 }
2334}

2337void BackgroundMergeTask::SetUpOnMainThread(
2338 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> cached_script) {
2339 // Any data sent to the background thread will need to be a persistent handle.
2340#ifdef DEBUG
2341 VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, cached_script);
2342#else
2343 if (v8_flags.verify_code_merge) {
2344 VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, cached_script);
2345 }
2346#endif
2347
2348 persistent_handles_ = std::make_unique<PersistentHandles>(isolate);
2349 state_ = kPendingBackgroundWork;
2350 cached_script_ = persistent_handles_->NewHandle(*cached_script);
2351}

2359void BackgroundMergeTask::BeginMergeInBackground(
2360 LocalIsolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> new_script) {
2361 DCHECK_EQ(state_, kPendingBackgroundWork);
2362
2363 LocalHeap* local_heap = isolate->heap();
2364 local_heap->AttachPersistentHandles(std::move(persistent_handles_));
2365 LocalHandleScope handle_scope(local_heap);
2366 DirectHandle<Script> old_script = cached_script_.ToHandleChecked();
2367 ConstantPoolPointerForwarder forwarder(isolate, local_heap, old_script);
2368
2369 {
2370 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2371 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_toplevel_sfi =
2372 old_script->infos()->get(kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel);
2373 if (maybe_old_toplevel_sfi.IsWeak()) {
2374 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> old_toplevel_sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(
2375 maybe_old_toplevel_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2376 toplevel_sfi_from_cached_script_ =
2377 local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(old_toplevel_sfi);
2378 }
2379 }
2380
2381 // Iterate the SFI lists on both Scripts to set up the forwarding table and
2382 // follow-up worklists for the main thread.
2383 CHECK_EQ(old_script->infos()->length(), new_script->infos()->length());
2384 for (int i = 0; i < old_script->infos()->length(); ++i) {
2385 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2386 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_new_sfi = new_script->infos()->get(i);
2387 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_info = old_script->infos()->get(i);
2388 // We might have scope infos in the table if it's deserialized from a code
2389 // cache.
2390 if (maybe_new_sfi.IsWeak() &&
2391 Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_new_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak())) {
2392 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> new_sfi =
2393 Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_new_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2394 if (maybe_old_info.IsWeak()) {
2395 forwarder.set_has_shared_function_info_to_forward();
2396 // The old script and the new script both have SharedFunctionInfos for
2397 // this function literal.
2398 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> old_sfi =
2399 Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_old_info.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2400 // Make sure to allocate a persistent handle to the old sfi whether or
2401 // not it or the new sfi have bytecode -- this is necessary to keep the
2402 // old sfi reference in the old script list alive, so that pointers to
2403 // the new sfi are redirected to the old sfi.
2404 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> old_sfi_handle =
2405 local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(old_sfi);
2406 if (old_sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2407 // Reset the old SFI's bytecode age so that it won't likely get
2408 // flushed right away. This operation might be racing against
2409 // concurrent modification by another thread, but such a race is not
2410 // catastrophic.
2411 old_sfi->set_age(0);
2412 } else if (new_sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2413 // Also push the old_sfi to make sure it stays alive / isn't replaced.
2414 new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_.push_back(
2415 {old_sfi_handle, local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(new_sfi)});
2416 if (old_sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2417 new_sfi->scope_info()->set_outer_scope_info(
2418 old_sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo());
2419 }
2420 forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(new_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2421 }
2422 } else {
2423 // The old script didn't have a SharedFunctionInfo for this function
2424 // literal, so it can use the new SharedFunctionInfo.
2425 new_sfi->set_script(*old_script, kReleaseStore);
2426 used_new_sfis_.push_back(local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(new_sfi));
2427 if (new_sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2428 forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(new_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2429 }
2430 }
2431 }
2432
2433 if (maybe_old_info.IsWeak()) {
2434 forwarder.RecordScopeInfos(maybe_old_info);
2435 // If the old script has a SFI, point to it from the new script to
2436 // indicate we've already seen it and we'll reuse it if necessary (if
2437 // newly compiled bytecode points to it).
2438 new_script->infos()->set(i, maybe_old_info);
2439 }
2440 }
2441
2442 // Since we are walking the script infos weak list both when figuring out
2443 // which SFIs to merge above, and actually merging them below, make sure that
2444 // a GC here which clears any dead weak refs or flushes any bytecode doesn't
2445 // break anything.
2446 if (V8_UNLIKELY(force_gc_during_next_merge_for_testing_)) {
2447 // This GC is only synchronous on the main thread at the moment.
2448 DCHECK(isolate->is_main_thread());
2449 local_heap->AsHeap()->CollectAllAvailableGarbage(
2450 GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting);
2451 }
2452
2453 if (forwarder.HasAnythingToForward()) {
2454 for (DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> new_sfi : used_new_sfis_) {
2455 forwarder.UpdateScopeInfo(*new_sfi);
2456 }
2457 for (const auto& new_compiled_data : new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_) {
2458 // It's possible that new_compiled_data.cached_sfi had
2459 // scope_info()->IsEmpty() while an inner function has scope info if the
2460 // cached_sfi was recreated when an outer function was recompiled. If so,
2461 // new_compiled_data.new_sfi does not have a reused scope info yet, and
2462 // we'll have found it when we visited the inner function. Try to pick it
2463 // up here.
2464 forwarder.InstallOwnScopeInfo(*new_compiled_data.new_sfi);
2465 }
2466 forwarder.IterateAndForwardPointers();
2467 }
2468 persistent_handles_ = local_heap->DetachPersistentHandles();
2469 state_ = kPendingForegroundWork;
2470}
2471
2472Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> BackgroundMergeTask::CompleteMergeInForeground(
2473 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> new_script) {
2474 DCHECK_EQ(state_, kPendingForegroundWork);
2475
2476 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2477 DirectHandle<Script> old_script = cached_script_.ToHandleChecked();
2478 ConstantPoolPointerForwarder forwarder(
2479 isolate, isolate->main_thread_local_heap(), old_script);
2480
2481 for (const auto& new_compiled_data : new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_) {
2482 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = *new_compiled_data.cached_sfi;
2483 if (!sfi->is_compiled() && new_compiled_data.new_sfi->is_compiled()) {
2484 // Updating existing DebugInfos is not supported, but we don't expect
2485 // uncompiled SharedFunctionInfos to contain DebugInfos.
2486 DCHECK(!new_compiled_data.cached_sfi->HasDebugInfo(isolate));
2487 // The goal here is to copy every field except script from
2488 // new_sfi to cached_sfi. The safest way to do so (including a DCHECK that
2489 // no fields were skipped) is to first copy the script from
2490 // cached_sfi to new_sfi, and then copy every field using CopyFrom.
2491 new_compiled_data.new_sfi->set_script(sfi->script(kAcquireLoad),
2492 kReleaseStore);
2493 sfi->CopyFrom(*new_compiled_data.new_sfi, isolate);
2494 }
2495 }
2496
2497 for (int i = 0; i < old_script->infos()->length(); ++i) {
2498 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_info = old_script->infos()->get(i);
2499 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_new_info = new_script->infos()->get(i);
2500 if (maybe_new_info == maybe_old_info) continue;
2501 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2502 if (maybe_old_info.IsWeak()) {
2503 // The old script's SFI didn't exist during the background work, but does
2504 // now. This means a re-merge is necessary. Potential references to the
2505 // new script's SFI need to be updated to point to the cached script's SFI
2506 // instead. The cached script's SFI's outer scope infos need to be used by
2507 // the new script's outer SFIs.
2508 if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_old_info.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak())) {
2509 forwarder.set_has_shared_function_info_to_forward();
2510 }
2511 forwarder.RecordScopeInfos(maybe_old_info);
2512 } else if (maybe_new_info.IsWeak() &&
2513 Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(
2514 maybe_new_info.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak())) {
2515 old_script->infos()->set(i, maybe_new_info);
2516 }
2517 }
2518
2519 // Most of the time, the background merge was sufficient. However, if there
2520 // are any new pointers that need forwarding, a new traversal of the constant
2521 // pools is required.
2522 if (forwarder.HasAnythingToForward()) {
2523 for (DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> new_sfi : used_new_sfis_) {
2524 forwarder.UpdateScopeInfo(*new_sfi);
2525 if (new_sfi->HasBytecodeArray(isolate)) {
2526 forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(new_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2527 }
2528 }
2529 for (const auto& new_compiled_data : new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_) {
2530 // It's possible that cached_sfi wasn't compiled, but an inner function
2531 // existed that didn't exist when be background merged. In that case, pick
2532 // up the relevant scope infos.
2533 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = *new_compiled_data.cached_sfi;
2534 forwarder.InstallOwnScopeInfo(sfi);
2535 if (new_compiled_data.cached_sfi->HasBytecodeArray(isolate)) {
2536 forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(
2537 new_compiled_data.cached_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2538 }
2539 }
2540 forwarder.IterateAndForwardPointers();
2541 }
2542
2543 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_toplevel_sfi =
2544 old_script->infos()->get(kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel);
2545 CHECK(maybe_toplevel_sfi.IsWeak());
2546 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> result = handle(
2547 Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_toplevel_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak()),
2548 isolate);
2549
2550 state_ = kDone;
2551
2552 if (isolate->NeedsSourcePositions()) {
2553 Script::InitLineEnds(isolate, new_script);
2554 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, result);
2555 }
2556
2557#ifdef DEBUG
2558 VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, old_script);
2559#else
2560 if (v8_flags.verify_code_merge) {
2561 VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, old_script);
2562 }
2563#endif
2564
2565 return handle_scope.CloseAndEscape(result);
2566}
2567
2568MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> BackgroundCompileTask::FinalizeScript(
2569 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> source,
2570 const ScriptDetails& script_details,
2571 MaybeDirectHandle<Script> maybe_cached_script) {
2572 ScriptOriginOptions origin_options = script_details.origin_options;
2573
2574 DCHECK(flags_.is_toplevel());
2575 DCHECK_EQ(flags_.is_module(), origin_options.IsModule());
2576
2577 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
2578 Handle<Script> script = script_;
2579
2580 // We might not have been able to finalize all jobs on the background
2581 // thread (e.g. asm.js jobs), so finalize those deferred jobs now.
2582 if (FinalizeDeferredUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2583 isolate, script, &jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread_,
2584 compile_state_.pending_error_handler(),
2585 &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_)) {
2586 maybe_result = outer_function_sfi_;
2587 }
2588
2589 if (DirectHandle<Script> cached_script;
2590 maybe_cached_script.ToHandle(&cached_script) && !maybe_result.is_null()) {
2591 BackgroundMergeTask merge;
2592 merge.SetUpOnMainThread(isolate, cached_script);
2593 CHECK(merge.HasPendingBackgroundWork());
2594 merge.BeginMergeInBackground(isolate->AsLocalIsolate(), script);
2595 CHECK(merge.HasPendingForegroundWork());
2596 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result =
2597 merge.CompleteMergeInForeground(isolate, script);
2598 maybe_result = result;
2599 script = handle(Cast<Script>(result->script()), isolate);
2600 DCHECK(Object::StrictEquals(script->source(), *source));
2601 DCHECK(isolate->factory()->script_list()->Contains(MakeWeak(*script)));
2602 } else {
2603 Script::SetSource(isolate, script, source);
2604 script->set_origin_options(origin_options);
2605
2606 // The one post-hoc fix-up: Add the script to the script list.
2607 Handle<WeakArrayList> scripts = isolate->factory()->script_list();
2608 scripts = WeakArrayList::Append(isolate, scripts,
2609 MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(script));
2610 isolate->heap()->SetRootScriptList(*scripts);
2611
2612 // Set the script fields after finalization, to keep this path the same
2613 // between main-thread and off-thread finalization.
2614 {
2615 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2616 SetScriptFieldsFromDetails(isolate, *script, script_details, &no_gc);
2617 LOG(isolate, ScriptDetails(*script));
2618 }
2619 }
2620
2621 ReportStatistics(isolate);
2622
2623 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
2624 if (!maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
2625 FailWithPreparedException(isolate, script,
2626 compile_state_.pending_error_handler());
2627 return kNullMaybeHandle;
2628 }
2629
2630 FinalizeUnoptimizedScriptCompilation(isolate, script, flags_, &compile_state_,
2631 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_);
2632
2633 return handle(*result, isolate);
2634}
2635
2636bool BackgroundCompileTask::FinalizeFunction(
2637 Isolate* isolate, Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag) {
2638 DCHECK(!flags_.is_toplevel());
2639
2640 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
2641 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> input_shared_info =
2642 input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked();
2643
2644 // The UncompiledData on the input SharedFunctionInfo will have a pointer to
2645 // the LazyCompileDispatcher Job that launched this task, which will now be
2646 // considered complete, so clear that regardless of whether the finalize
2647 // succeeds or not.
2648 input_shared_info->ClearUncompiledDataJobPointer(isolate);
2649
2650 // We might not have been able to finalize all jobs on the background
2651 // thread (e.g. asm.js jobs), so finalize those deferred jobs now.
2652 if (FinalizeDeferredUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2653 isolate, script_, &jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread_,
2654 compile_state_.pending_error_handler(),
2655 &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_)) {
2656 maybe_result = outer_function_sfi_;
2657 }
2658
2659 ReportStatistics(isolate);
2660
2661 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
2662 if (!maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
2663 FailWithPreparedException(isolate, script_,
2664 compile_state_.pending_error_handler(), flag);
2665 return false;
2666 }
2667
2668 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, script_, flags_, &compile_state_,
2669 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_);
2670
2671 // Move the compiled data from the placeholder SFI back to the real SFI.
2672 input_shared_info->CopyFrom(*result, isolate);
2673
2674 return true;
2675}
2676
2677void BackgroundCompileTask::AbortFunction() {
2678 // The UncompiledData on the input SharedFunctionInfo will have a pointer to
2679 // the LazyCompileDispatcher Job that launched this task, which is about to be
2680 // deleted, so clear that to avoid the SharedFunctionInfo from pointing to
2681 // deallocated memory.
2682 input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked()->ClearUncompiledDataJobPointer(
2683 isolate_for_local_isolate_);
2684}
2685
2686void BackgroundCompileTask::ReportStatistics(Isolate* isolate) {
2687 // Update use-counts.
2688 for (auto feature : use_counts_) {
2689 isolate->CountUsage(feature);
2690 }
2691}

2758// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2759// Implementation of Compiler
2760
2761// static
2762bool Compiler::CollectSourcePositions(
2763 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info) {
2764 DCHECK(shared_info->is_compiled());
2765 DCHECK(shared_info->HasBytecodeArray());
2766 DCHECK(!shared_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)->HasSourcePositionTable());
2767
2768 // Source position collection should be context independent.
2769 NullContextScope null_context_scope(isolate);
2770
2771 // Collecting source positions requires allocating a new source position
2772 // table.
2773 DCHECK(AllowHeapAllocation::IsAllowed());
2774
2775 Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode =
2776 handle(shared_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate), isolate);
2777
2778 // TODO(v8:8510): Push the CLEAR_EXCEPTION flag or something like it down into
2779 // the parser so it aborts without setting an exception, which then
2780 // gets thrown. This would avoid the situation where potentially we'd reparse
2781 // several times (running out of stack each time) before hitting this limit.
2782 if (GetCurrentStackPosition() < isolate->stack_guard()->real_climit()) {
2783 // Stack is already exhausted.
2784 bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2785 return false;
2786 }
2787
2788 // Unfinalized scripts don't yet have the proper source string attached and
2789 // thus can't be reparsed.
2790 if (Cast<Script>(shared_info->script())->IsMaybeUnfinalized(isolate)) {
2791 bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2792 return false;
2793 }
2794
2795 DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
2796 DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
2797
2798 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
2799 VMState<BYTECODE_COMPILER> state(isolate);
2800 PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
2801 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileCollectSourcePositions);
2802 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2803 "V8.CollectSourcePositions");
2804 NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(
2805 isolate->counters()->collect_source_positions());
2806
2807 // Set up parse info.
2808 UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
2809 UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForFunctionCompile(isolate, *shared_info);
2810 flags.set_collect_source_positions(true);
2811 flags.set_is_reparse(true);
2812 // Prevent parallel tasks from being spawned by this job.
2813 flags.set_post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_eager_toplevel(false);
2814 flags.set_post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_lazy(false);
2815
2816 UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
2817 ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
2818 ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
2819
2820 // Parse and update ParseInfo with the results. Don't update parsing
2821 // statistics since we've already parsed the code before.
2822 if (!parsing::ParseAny(&parse_info, shared_info, isolate,
2823 parsing::ReportStatisticsMode::kNo)) {
2824 // Parsing failed probably as a result of stack exhaustion.
2825 bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2826 return FailAndClearException(isolate);
2827 }
2828
2829 // Character stream shouldn't be used again.
2830 parse_info.ResetCharacterStream();
2831
2832 // Generate the unoptimized bytecode.
2833 // TODO(v8:8510): Consider forcing preparsing of inner functions to avoid
2834 // wasting time fully parsing them when they won't ever be used.
2835 std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> job;
2836 {
2837 job = interpreter::Interpreter::NewSourcePositionCollectionJob(
2838 &parse_info, parse_info.literal(), bytecode, isolate->allocator(),
2839 isolate->main_thread_local_isolate());
2840
2841 if (!job || job->ExecuteJob() != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED ||
2842 job->FinalizeJob(shared_info, isolate) != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
2843 // Recompiling failed probably as a result of stack exhaustion.
2844 bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2845 return FailAndClearException(isolate);
2846 }
2847 }
2848
2849 DCHECK(job->compilation_info()->flags().collect_source_positions());
2850
2851 // If debugging, make sure that instrumented bytecode has the source position
2852 // table set on it as well.
2853 if (std::optional<Tagged<DebugInfo>> debug_info =
2854 shared_info->TryGetDebugInfo(isolate)) {
2855 if (debug_info.value()->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray()) {
2856 Tagged<TrustedByteArray> source_position_table =
2857 job->compilation_info()->bytecode_array()->SourcePositionTable();
2858 shared_info->GetActiveBytecodeArray(isolate)->set_source_position_table(
2859 source_position_table, kReleaseStore);
2860 }
2861 }
2862
2863 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
2864 DCHECK(shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate).is_compiled());
2865 return true;
2866}
2867
2868// static
2869bool Compiler::Compile(Isolate* isolate, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
2870 ClearExceptionFlag flag,
2871 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope,
2872 CreateSourcePositions create_source_positions_flag) {
2873 // We should never reach here if the function is already compiled.
2874 DCHECK(!shared_info->is_compiled());
2875 DCHECK(!is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
2876 DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
2877 DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
2878 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
2879 DCHECK(!shared_info->HasBytecodeArray());
2880
2881 VMState<BYTECODE_COMPILER> state(isolate);
2882 PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
2883 TimerEventScope<TimerEventCompileCode> compile_timer(isolate);
2884 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileFunction);
2885 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.CompileCode");
2886 AggregatedHistogramTimerScope timer(isolate->counters()->compile_lazy());
2887
2888 Handle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()), isolate);
2889
2890 // Set up parse info.
2891 UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
2892 UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForFunctionCompile(isolate, *shared_info);
2893 if (create_source_positions_flag == CreateSourcePositions::kYes) {
2894 flags.set_collect_source_positions(true);
2895 }
2896
2897 UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
2898 ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
2899 ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
2900
2901 // Check if the compiler dispatcher has shared_info enqueued for compile.
2902 LazyCompileDispatcher* dispatcher = isolate->lazy_compile_dispatcher();
2903 if (dispatcher && dispatcher->IsEnqueued(shared_info)) {
2904 if (!dispatcher->FinishNow(shared_info)) {
2905 return FailWithException(isolate, script, &parse_info, flag);
2906 }
2907 *is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
2908 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
2909 return true;
2910 }
2911
2912 if (shared_info->HasUncompiledDataWithPreparseData()) {
2913 parse_info.set_consumed_preparse_data(ConsumedPreparseData::For(
2914 isolate, handle(shared_info->uncompiled_data_with_preparse_data(isolate)
2915 ->preparse_data(),
2916 isolate)));
2917 }
2918
2919 // Parse and update ParseInfo with the results.
2920 if (!parsing::ParseAny(&parse_info, shared_info, isolate,
2921 parsing::ReportStatisticsMode::kYes)) {
2922 return FailWithException(isolate, script, &parse_info, flag);
2923 }
2924 parse_info.literal()->set_shared_function_info(shared_info);
2925
2926 // Generate the unoptimized bytecode or asm-js data.
2927 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList
2928 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list;
2929
2930 if (!IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2931 isolate, script, &parse_info, isolate->allocator(), is_compiled_scope,
2932 &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list, nullptr)) {
2933 return FailWithException(isolate, script, &parse_info, flag);
2934 }
2935
2936 FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, script, flags, &compile_state,
2937 finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
2938
2939 if (v8_flags.always_sparkplug) {
2940 CompileAllWithBaseline(isolate, finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
2941 }
2942
2943 if (script->produce_compile_hints()) {
2944 // Log lazy funtion compilation.
2945 Handle<ArrayList> list;
2946 if (IsUndefined(script->compiled_lazy_function_positions())) {
2947 constexpr int kInitialLazyFunctionPositionListSize = 100;
2948 list = ArrayList::New(isolate, kInitialLazyFunctionPositionListSize);
2949 } else {
2950 list = handle(Cast<ArrayList>(script->compiled_lazy_function_positions()),
2951 isolate);
2952 }
2953 list = ArrayList::Add(isolate, list,
2954 Smi::FromInt(shared_info->StartPosition()));
2955 script->set_compiled_lazy_function_positions(*list);
2956 }
2957
2958 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
2959 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
2960 return true;
2961}

2963// static
2964bool Compiler::Compile(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
2965 ClearExceptionFlag flag,
2966 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
2967 // We should never reach here if the function is already compiled or
2968 // optimized.
2969 DCHECK(!function->is_compiled(isolate));
2970 DCHECK_IMPLIES(function->has_feedback_vector() &&
2971 function->IsTieringRequestedOrInProgress(isolate),
2972 function->shared()->is_compiled());
2973 DCHECK_IMPLIES(function->HasAvailableOptimizedCode(isolate),
2974 function->shared()->is_compiled());
2975
2976 // Reset the JSFunction if we are recompiling due to the bytecode having been
2977 // flushed.
2978 function->ResetIfCodeFlushed(isolate);
2979
2980 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info(function->shared(), isolate);
2981
2982 // Ensure shared function info is compiled.
2983 *is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
2984 if (!is_compiled_scope->is_compiled() &&
2985 !Compile(isolate, shared_info, flag, is_compiled_scope)) {
2986 return false;
2987 }
2988
2989 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
2990 DirectHandle<Code> code(shared_info->GetCode(isolate), isolate);
2991
2992 // Initialize the feedback cell for this JSFunction and reset the interrupt
2993 // budget for feedback vector allocation even if there is a closure feedback
2994 // cell array. We are re-compiling when we have a closure feedback cell array
2995 // which means we are compiling after a bytecode flush.
2996 // TODO(verwaest/mythria): Investigate if allocating feedback vector
2997 // immediately after a flush would be better.
2998 JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(function, is_compiled_scope, true);
2999 function->ResetTieringRequests(isolate);
3000
3001 function->UpdateCode(*code);
3002
3003 // Optimize now if --always-turbofan is enabled.
3004#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3005 if (v8_flags.always_turbofan && !function->shared()->HasAsmWasmData()) {
3006#else
3007 if (v8_flags.always_turbofan) {
3008#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3009 DCHECK(!function->tiering_in_progress());
3010 CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeForAlwaysOpt(isolate, function,
3011 CodeKindForTopTier());
3012
3013 const CodeKind code_kind = CodeKindForTopTier();
3014 const ConcurrencyMode concurrency_mode = ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous;
3015
3016 if (v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining &&
3017 isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled() &&
3018 isolate->node_observer() == nullptr) {
3019 SpawnDuplicateConcurrentJobForStressTesting(isolate, function,
3020 concurrency_mode, code_kind);
3021 }
3022
3023 DirectHandle<Code> maybe_code;
3024 if (GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, concurrency_mode, code_kind)
3025 .ToHandle(&maybe_code)) {
3026 code = maybe_code;
3027 function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, *code);
3028 }
3029 }
3030
3031 // Install a feedback vector if necessary.
3032 if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE) {
3033 JSFunction::EnsureFeedbackVector(isolate, function, is_compiled_scope);
3034 }
3035
3036 // Check postconditions on success.
3037 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
3038 DCHECK(function->shared()->is_compiled());
3039 DCHECK(function->is_compiled(isolate));
3040 return true;
3041}

3043// static
3044bool Compiler::CompileSharedWithBaseline(Isolate* isolate,
3045 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
3046 Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag,
3047 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
3048 // We shouldn't be passing uncompiled functions into this function.
3049 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
3050
3051 // Early return for already baseline-compiled functions.
3052 if (shared->HasBaselineCode()) return true;
3053
3054 // Check if we actually can compile with baseline.
3055 if (!CanCompileWithBaseline(isolate, *shared)) return false;
3056
3057 StackLimitCheck check(isolate);
3058 if (check.JsHasOverflowed(kStackSpaceRequiredForCompilation * KB)) {
3059 if (flag == Compiler::KEEP_EXCEPTION) {
3060 isolate->StackOverflow();
3061 }
3062 return false;
3063 }
3064
3065 CompilerTracer::TraceStartBaselineCompile(isolate, shared);
3066 Handle<Code> code;
3067 base::TimeDelta time_taken;
3068 {
3069 base::ScopedTimer timer(
3070 v8_flags.trace_baseline || v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken
3071 : nullptr);
3072 if (!GenerateBaselineCode(isolate, shared).ToHandle(&code)) {
3073 // TODO(leszeks): This can only fail because of an OOM. Do we want to
3074 // report these somehow, or silently ignore them?
3075 return false;
3076 }
3077 shared->set_baseline_code(*code, kReleaseStore);
3078 shared->set_age(0);
3079 }
3080 double time_taken_ms = time_taken.InMillisecondsF();
3081
3082 CompilerTracer::TraceFinishBaselineCompile(isolate, shared, time_taken_ms);
3083
3084 if (IsScript(shared->script())) {
3085 LogFunctionCompilation(
3086 isolate, LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction,
3087 direct_handle(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate), shared,
3088 DirectHandle<FeedbackVector>(), Cast<AbstractCode>(code),
3089 CodeKind::BASELINE, time_taken_ms);
3090 }
3091 return true;
3092}

3097 ClearExceptionFlag flag,
3098 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {

3100 if (!CompileSharedWithBaseline(isolate, shared, flag, is_compiled_scope)) {
3101 return false;
3102 }

3110 return true;

3138// static
3139void Compiler::CompileOptimized(Isolate* isolate,
3140 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
3141 ConcurrencyMode mode, CodeKind code_kind) {
3142 DCHECK(CodeKindIsOptimizedJSFunction(code_kind));
3143 DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
3144
3145 if (v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining &&
3146 isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled() && IsSynchronous(mode) &&
3147 isolate->node_observer() == nullptr) {
3148 SpawnDuplicateConcurrentJobForStressTesting(isolate, function, mode,
3149 code_kind);
3150 }
3151
3152#ifdef DEBUG
3153 if (V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL && mode == ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent) {
3154 DCHECK_IMPLIES(code_kind == CodeKind::MAGLEV,
3155 !function->ActiveTierIsMaglev(isolate));
3156 DCHECK_IMPLIES(code_kind == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS,
3157 !function->ActiveTierIsTurbofan(isolate));
3158 }
3159 bool tiering_was_in_progress = function->tiering_in_progress();
3160 DCHECK_IMPLIES(tiering_was_in_progress, mode != ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent);
3161#endif // DEBUG
3162
3163 DirectHandle<Code> code;
3164 if (GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, mode, code_kind)
3165 .ToHandle(&code)) {
3166 function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, *code);
3167 DCHECK_IMPLIES(v8_flags.log_function_events,
3168 function->IsLoggingRequested(isolate));
3169 } else {
3170#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3171 // We can get here from CompileLazy when we have requested optimized code
3172 // which isn't yet ready. Without Leaptiering, we'll already have set the
3173 // function's code to the bytecode/baseline code on the SFI. However, in the
3174 // leaptiering case, we potentially need to do this now.
3175 if (!function->is_compiled(isolate)) {
3176 function->UpdateCodeKeepTieringRequests(
3177 function->shared()->GetCode(isolate));
3178 }
3179#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3180 }
3181
3182#ifdef DEBUG
3183 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
3184 DCHECK(function->is_compiled(isolate));
3185 DCHECK(function->shared()->HasBytecodeArray());
3186
3187 DCHECK_IMPLIES(function->IsTieringRequestedOrInProgress(isolate) &&
3188 !function->IsLoggingRequested(isolate),
3189 function->tiering_in_progress());
3190 if (!v8_flags.always_turbofan) {
3191 // Before a maglev optimization job is started we might have to compile
3192 // bytecode. This can trigger a turbofan compilation if always_turbofan is
3193 // set. Therefore we need to skip this dcheck in that case.
3194 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!tiering_was_in_progress && function->tiering_in_progress(),
3195 function->ChecksTieringState(isolate));
3196 }
3197 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!tiering_was_in_progress && function->tiering_in_progress(),
3198 IsConcurrent(mode));
3199#endif // DEBUG
3200}

3211// static
3212MaybeHandle<JSFunction> Compiler::GetFunctionFromEval(
3213 Handle<String> source, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info,
3214 DirectHandle<Context> context, LanguageMode language_mode,
3215 ParseRestriction restriction, int parameters_end_pos, int eval_position,
3216 ParsingWhileDebugging parsing_while_debugging) {
3217 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
3218
3219 // The cache lookup key needs to be aware of the separation between the
3220 // parameters and the body to prevent this valid invocation:
3221 // Function("", "function anonymous(\n/**/) {\n}");
3222 // from adding an entry that falsely approves this invalid invocation:
3223 // Function("\n/**/) {\nfunction anonymous(", "}");
3224 // The actual eval_position for indirect eval and CreateDynamicFunction
3225 // is unused (just 0), which means it's an available field to use to indicate
3226 // this separation. But to make sure we're not causing other false hits, we
3227 // negate the scope position.
3228 int eval_cache_position = eval_position;
3229 if (restriction == ONLY_SINGLE_FUNCTION_LITERAL &&
3230 parameters_end_pos != kNoSourcePosition) {
3231 // use the parameters_end_pos as the eval_position in the eval cache.
3232 DCHECK_EQ(eval_position, kNoSourcePosition);
3233 eval_cache_position = -parameters_end_pos;
3234 }
3235 CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
3236 InfoCellPair eval_result = compilation_cache->LookupEval(
3237 source, outer_info, context, language_mode, eval_cache_position);
3238 DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell;
3239 if (eval_result.has_feedback_cell()) {
3240 feedback_cell = direct_handle(eval_result.feedback_cell(), isolate);
3241 }
3242
3243 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info;
3244 Handle<Script> script;
3245 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
3246 bool allow_eval_cache;
3247 if (eval_result.has_shared()) {
3248 shared_info =
3249 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>(eval_result.shared(), isolate);
3250 script = Handle<Script>(Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()), isolate);
3251 is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
3252 allow_eval_cache = true;
3253 } else {
3254 UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags = UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForToplevelCompile(
3255 isolate, true, language_mode, REPLMode::kNo, ScriptType::kClassic,
3256 v8_flags.lazy_eval);
3257 flags.set_is_eval(true);
3258 flags.set_parsing_while_debugging(parsing_while_debugging);
3259 DCHECK(!flags.is_module());
3260 flags.set_parse_restriction(restriction);
3261
3262 UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
3263 ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
3264 ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
3265 parse_info.set_parameters_end_pos(parameters_end_pos);
3266
3267 MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info;
3268 if (!IsNativeContext(*context)) {
3269 maybe_outer_scope_info = direct_handle(context->scope_info(), isolate);
3270 }
3271 script = parse_info.CreateScript(
3272 isolate, source, kNullMaybeHandle,
3273 OriginOptionsForEval(outer_info->script(), parsing_while_debugging));
3274 script->set_eval_from_shared(*outer_info);
3275 if (eval_position == kNoSourcePosition) {
3276 // If the position is missing, attempt to get the code offset by
3277 // walking the stack. Do not translate the code offset into source
3278 // position, but store it as negative value for lazy translation.
3279 DebuggableStackFrameIterator it(isolate);
3280 if (!it.done() && it.is_javascript()) {
3281 FrameSummary summary = it.GetTopValidFrame();
3282 script->set_eval_from_shared(
3283 summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared());
3284 script->set_origin_options(
3285 OriginOptionsForEval(*summary.script(), parsing_while_debugging));
3286 eval_position = -summary.code_offset();
3287 } else {
3288 eval_position = 0;
3289 }
3290 }
3291 script->set_eval_from_position(eval_position);
3292
3293 if (!v8::internal::CompileToplevel(&parse_info, script,
3294 maybe_outer_scope_info, isolate,
3295 &is_compiled_scope)
3296 .ToHandle(&shared_info)) {
3297 return MaybeHandle<JSFunction>();
3298 }
3299 allow_eval_cache = parse_info.allow_eval_cache();
3300 }
3301
3302 // If caller is strict mode, the result must be in strict mode as well.
3303 DCHECK(is_sloppy(language_mode) || is_strict(shared_info->language_mode()));
3304
3305 Handle<JSFunction> result;
3306 if (eval_result.has_shared()) {
3307 if (eval_result.has_feedback_cell()) {
3308 result = Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, shared_info, context}
3309 .set_feedback_cell(feedback_cell)
3310 .set_allocation_type(AllocationType::kYoung)
3311 .Build();
3312 } else {
3313 result = Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, shared_info, context}
3314 .set_allocation_type(AllocationType::kYoung)
3315 .Build();
3316 // TODO(mythria): I don't think we need this here. PostInstantiation
3317 // already initializes feedback cell.
3318 JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(result, &is_compiled_scope, true);
3319 if (allow_eval_cache) {
3320 // Make sure to cache this result.
3321 DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> new_feedback_cell(
3322 result->raw_feedback_cell(), isolate);
3323 compilation_cache->PutEval(source, outer_info, context, shared_info,
3324 new_feedback_cell, eval_cache_position);
3325 }
3326 }
3327 } else {
3328 result = Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, shared_info, context}
3329 .set_allocation_type(AllocationType::kYoung)
3330 .Build();
3331 // TODO(mythria): I don't think we need this here. PostInstantiation
3332 // already initializes feedback cell.
3333 JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(result, &is_compiled_scope, true);
3334 if (allow_eval_cache) {
3335 // Add the SharedFunctionInfo and the LiteralsArray to the eval cache if
3336 // we didn't retrieve from there.
3337 DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> new_feedback_cell(result->raw_feedback_cell(),
3338 isolate);
3339 compilation_cache->PutEval(source, outer_info, context, shared_info,
3340 new_feedback_cell, eval_cache_position);
3341 }
3342 }
3343 CHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
3344
3345 return result;
3346}
3347
3348// Check whether embedder allows code generation in this context.
3349// (via v8::Isolate::SetModifyCodeGenerationFromStringsCallback)
3350bool ModifyCodeGenerationFromStrings(Isolate* isolate,
3351 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context,
3352 Handle<i::Object>* source,
3353 bool is_code_like) {
3354 DCHECK(isolate->modify_code_gen_callback());
3355 DCHECK(source);
3356
3357 // Callback set. Run it, and use the return value as source, or block
3358 // execution if it's not set.
3359 VMState<EXTERNAL> state(isolate);
3360 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCodeGenerationFromStringsCallbacks);
3361 ModifyCodeGenerationFromStringsResult result =
3362 isolate->modify_code_gen_callback()(v8::Utils::ToLocal(context),
3363 v8::Utils::ToLocal(*source),
3364 is_code_like);
3365 if (result.codegen_allowed && !result.modified_source.IsEmpty()) {
3366 // Use the new source (which might be the same as the old source).
3367 *source =
3368 Utils::OpenHandle(*result.modified_source.ToLocalChecked(), false);
3369 }
3370 return result.codegen_allowed;
3371}
3372
3373// Run Embedder-mandated checks before generating code from a string.
3374//
3375// Returns a string to be used for compilation, or a flag that an object type
3376// was encountered that is neither a string, nor something the embedder knows
3377// how to handle.
3378//
3379// Returns: (assuming: std::tie(source, unknown_object))
3380// - !source.is_null(): compilation allowed, source contains the source string.
3381// - unknown_object is true: compilation allowed, but we don't know how to
3382// deal with source_object.
3383// - source.is_null() && !unknown_object: compilation should be blocked.
3384//
3385// - !source_is_null() and unknown_object can't be true at the same time.
3386
3387// static
3388std::pair<MaybeHandle<String>, bool> Compiler::ValidateDynamicCompilationSource(
3389 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> context,
3390 Handle<i::Object> original_source, bool is_code_like) {
3391 // Check if the context unconditionally allows code gen from strings.
3392 // allow_code_gen_from_strings can be many things, so we'll always check
3393 // against the 'false' literal, so that e.g. undefined and 'true' are treated
3394 // the same.
3395 if (!IsFalse(context->allow_code_gen_from_strings(), isolate) &&
3396 IsString(*original_source)) {
3397 return {Cast<String>(original_source), false};
3398 }
3399
3400 // Check if the context wants to block or modify this source object.
3401 // Double-check that we really have a string now.
3402 // (Let modify_code_gen_callback decide, if it's been set.)
3403 if (isolate->modify_code_gen_callback()) {
3404 Handle<i::Object> modified_source = original_source;
3405 if (!ModifyCodeGenerationFromStrings(isolate, context, &modified_source,
3406 is_code_like)) {
3407 return {MaybeHandle<String>(), false};
3408 }
3409 if (!IsString(*modified_source)) {
3410 return {MaybeHandle<String>(), true};
3411 }
3412 return {Cast<String>(modified_source), false};
3413 }
3414
3415 if (!IsFalse(context->allow_code_gen_from_strings(), isolate) &&
3416 Object::IsCodeLike(*original_source, isolate)) {
3417 // Codegen is unconditionally allowed, and we're been given a CodeLike
3418 // object. Stringify.
3419 MaybeHandle<String> stringified_source =
3420 Object::ToString(isolate, original_source);
3421 return {stringified_source, stringified_source.is_null()};
3422 }
3423
3424 // If unconditional codegen was disabled, and no callback defined, we block
3425 // strings and allow all other objects.
3426 return {MaybeHandle<String>(), !IsString(*original_source)};
3427}

3430MaybeHandle<JSFunction> Compiler::GetFunctionFromValidatedString(
3431 DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context, MaybeHandle<String> source,
3432 ParseRestriction restriction, int parameters_end_pos) {
3433 Isolate* const isolate = native_context->GetIsolate();
3434
3435 // Raise an EvalError if we did not receive a string.
3436 if (source.is_null()) {
3437 Handle<Object> error_message =
3438 native_context->ErrorMessageForCodeGenerationFromStrings();
3439 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewEvalError(MessageTemplate::kCodeGenFromStrings,
3440 error_message));
3441 }
3442
3443 // Compile source string in the native context.
3444 int eval_position = kNoSourcePosition;
3445 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info(
3446 native_context->empty_function()->shared(), isolate);
3447 return Compiler::GetFunctionFromEval(
3448 source.ToHandleChecked(), outer_info, native_context,
3449 LanguageMode::kSloppy, restriction, parameters_end_pos, eval_position);

3514 DCHECK_EQ(0, cache_behaviour_histogram->min());
3515 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(CacheBehaviour::kCount),
3516 cache_behaviour_histogram->max() + 1);
3517 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(CacheBehaviour::kCount),
3518 cache_behaviour_histogram->num_buckets());
3519 cache_behaviour_histogram->AddSample(static_cast<int>(cache_behaviour));
3520
3521 histogram_scope_.set_histogram(
3522 GetCacheBehaviourTimedHistogram(cache_behaviour));
3523 }
3524
3525 void set_hit_isolate_cache() { hit_isolate_cache_ = true; }
3526
3527 void set_consuming_code_cache() { consuming_code_cache_ = true; }
3528
3529 void set_consuming_code_cache_failed() {
3530 consuming_code_cache_failed_ = true;
3531 }
3532
3533 private:
3534 Isolate* isolate_;
3535 LazyTimedHistogramScope histogram_scope_;
3536 // TODO(leszeks): This timer is the sum of the other times, consider removing
3537 // it to save space.
3538 NestedTimedHistogramScope all_scripts_histogram_scope_;
3539 ScriptCompiler::NoCacheReason no_cache_reason_;
3540 bool hit_isolate_cache_;
3541 bool consuming_code_cache_;
3542 bool consuming_code_cache_failed_;
3543
3544 CacheBehaviour GetCacheBehaviour() {
3545 if (consuming_code_cache_) {
3546 if (hit_isolate_cache_) {
3547 return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenConsumeCodeCache;
3548 } else if (consuming_code_cache_failed_) {
3549 return CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCacheFailed;
3550 }
3551 return CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCache;
3552 }
3553
3554 if (hit_isolate_cache_) {
3555 // A roundabout way of knowing the embedder is going to produce a code
3556 // cache (which is done by a separate API call later) is to check whether
3557 // no_cache_reason_ is
3558 // ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseDeferredProduceCodeCache.
3559 if (no_cache_reason_ ==
3560 ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseDeferredProduceCodeCache) {
3561 return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenProduceCodeCache;
3562 } else if (no_cache_reason_ ==
3563 ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource) {
3564 return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenStreamingSource;
3565 }
3566 return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenNoCache;
3567 }
3568
3569 switch (no_cache_reason_) {
3570 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseInlineScript:
3571 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInlineScript;
3572 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseScriptTooSmall:
3573 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseScriptTooSmall;
3574 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseCacheTooCold:
3575 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCacheTooCold;
3576 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheNoReason:
3577 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheNoReason;
3578 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseNoResource:
3579 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseNoResource;
3580 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseInspector:
3581 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInspector;
3582 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseCachingDisabled:
3583 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCachingDisabled;
3584 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseModule:
3585 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseModule;
3586 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource:
3587 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource;
3588 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseV8Extension:
3589 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseV8Extension;
3590 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseExtensionModule:
3591 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseExtensionModule;
3592 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecausePacScript:
3593 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecausePacScript;
3594 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseInDocumentWrite:
3595 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInDocumentWrite;
3596 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseResourceWithNoCacheHandler:
3597 return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseResourceWithNoCacheHandler;
3598 case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseDeferredProduceCodeCache:
3599 return CacheBehaviour::kProduceCodeCache;
3600 }
3601 UNREACHABLE();
3602 }
3603
3604 TimedHistogram* GetCacheBehaviourTimedHistogram(
3605 CacheBehaviour cache_behaviour) {
3606 switch (cache_behaviour) {
3607 case CacheBehaviour::kProduceCodeCache:
3608 // Even if we hit the isolate's compilation cache, we currently recompile
3609 // when we want to produce the code cache.
3610 case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenProduceCodeCache:
3611 return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_with_produce_cache();
3612 case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenNoCache:
3613 case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenConsumeCodeCache:
3614 case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenStreamingSource:
3615 return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_with_isolate_cache_hit();
3616 case CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCacheFailed:
3617 return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_consume_failed();
3618 case CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCache:
3619 return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_with_consume_cache();
3620
3621 // Note that this only counts the finalization part of streaming, the
3622 // actual streaming compile is counted by BackgroundCompileTask into
3623 // "compile_script_on_background".
3624 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource:
3625 return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_streaming_finalization();
3626
3627 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInlineScript:
3628 return isolate_->counters()
3629 ->compile_script_no_cache_because_inline_script();
3630 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseScriptTooSmall:
3631 return isolate_->counters()
3632 ->compile_script_no_cache_because_script_too_small();
3633 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCacheTooCold:
3634 return isolate_->counters()
3635 ->compile_script_no_cache_because_cache_too_cold();
3636
3637 // Aggregate all the other "no cache" counters into a single histogram, to
3638 // save space.
3639 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheNoReason:
3640 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseNoResource:
3641 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInspector:
3642 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCachingDisabled:
3643 // TODO(leszeks): Consider counting separately once modules are more
3644 // common.
3645 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseModule:
3646 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseV8Extension:
3647 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseExtensionModule:
3648 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecausePacScript:
3649 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInDocumentWrite:
3650 case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseResourceWithNoCacheHandler:
3651 return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_no_cache_other();
3652
3653 case CacheBehaviour::kCount:
3654 UNREACHABLE();
3655 }
3656 UNREACHABLE();
3657 }
3658};

3660Handle<Script> NewScript(Isolate* isolate, ParseInfo* parse_info,
3661 Handle<String> source, ScriptDetails script_details,
3662 NativesFlag natives) {
3663 // Create a script object describing the script to be compiled.
3664 Handle<Script> script = parse_info->CreateScript(
3665 isolate, source, script_details.wrapped_arguments,
3666 script_details.origin_options, natives);
3667 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3668 SetScriptFieldsFromDetails(isolate, *script, script_details, &no_gc);
3669 LOG(isolate, ScriptDetails(*script));
3670 return script;
3671}
3672
3673MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> CompileScriptOnMainThread(
3674 const UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags, Handle<String> source,
3675 const ScriptDetails& script_details, NativesFlag natives,
3676 v8::Extension* extension, Isolate* isolate,
3677 MaybeHandle<Script> maybe_script, IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope,
3678 CompileHintCallback compile_hint_callback = nullptr,
3679 void* compile_hint_callback_data = nullptr) {
3680 UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
3681 ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
3682 ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
3683 parse_info.set_extension(extension);
3684 parse_info.SetCompileHintCallbackAndData(compile_hint_callback,
3685 compile_hint_callback_data);
3686
3687 Handle<Script> script;
3688 if (!maybe_script.ToHandle(&script)) {
3689 script = NewScript(isolate, &parse_info, source, script_details, natives);
3690 }
3691 DCHECK_EQ(parse_info.flags().is_repl_mode(), script->is_repl_mode());
3692
3693 return Compiler::CompileToplevel(&parse_info, script, isolate,
3694 is_compiled_scope);
3695}

3697class StressBackgroundCompileThread : public ParkingThread {
3698 public:
3699 StressBackgroundCompileThread(Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> source,
3700 const ScriptDetails& script_details)
3701 : ParkingThread(
3702 base::Thread::Options("StressBackgroundCompileThread", 2 * i::MB)),
3703 source_(source),
3704 streamed_source_(std::make_unique<SourceStream>(source, isolate),
3705 v8::ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource::TWO_BYTE) {
3706 ScriptType type = script_details.origin_options.IsModule()
3707 ? ScriptType::kModule
3708 : ScriptType::kClassic;
3709 data()->task = std::make_unique<i::BackgroundCompileTask>(
3710 data(), isolate, type,
3711 ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions::kNoCompileOptions,
3712 &streamed_source_.compilation_details());
3713 }
3714
3715 void Run() override { data()->task->Run(); }
3716
3717 ScriptStreamingData* data() { return streamed_source_.impl(); }
3718
3719 private:
3720 // Dummy external source stream which returns the whole source in one go.
3721 // TODO(leszeks): Also test chunking the data.
3722 class SourceStream : public v8::ScriptCompiler::ExternalSourceStream {
3723 public:
3724 SourceStream(DirectHandle<String> source, Isolate* isolate) : done_(false) {
3725 source_length_ = source->length();
3726 source_buffer_ = std::make_unique<uint16_t[]>(source_length_);
3727 String::WriteToFlat(*source, source_buffer_.get(), 0, source_length_);
3728 }
3729
3730 size_t GetMoreData(const uint8_t** src) override {
3731 if (done_) {
3732 return 0;
3733 }
3734 *src = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(source_buffer_.release());
3735 done_ = true;
3736
3737 return source_length_ * 2;
3738 }
3739
3740 private:
3741 uint32_t source_length_;
3742 std::unique_ptr<uint16_t[]> source_buffer_;
3743 bool done_;
3744 };
3745
3746 Handle<String> source_;
3747 v8::ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource streamed_source_;
3748};

3750bool CanBackgroundCompile(const ScriptDetails& script_details,
3751 v8::Extension* extension,
3752 ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions compile_options,
3753 NativesFlag natives) {
3754 // TODO(leszeks): Remove the module check once background compilation of
3755 // modules is supported.
3756 return !script_details.origin_options.IsModule() && !extension &&
3757 script_details.repl_mode == REPLMode::kNo &&
3758 (compile_options == ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions) &&
3759 natives == NOT_NATIVES_CODE;
3760}

3762bool CompilationExceptionIsRangeError(Isolate* isolate,
3763 DirectHandle<Object> obj) {
3764 if (!IsJSError(*obj, isolate)) return false;
3765 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> js_obj = Cast<JSReceiver>(obj);
3766 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> constructor;
3767 if (!JSReceiver::GetConstructor(isolate, js_obj).ToHandle(&constructor)) {
3768 return false;
3769 }
3770 return *constructor == *isolate->range_error_function();
3771}
3772
3773MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>
3774CompileScriptOnBothBackgroundAndMainThread(Handle<String> source,
3775 const ScriptDetails& script_details,
3776 Isolate* isolate,
3777 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
3778 // Start a background thread compiling the script.
3779 StressBackgroundCompileThread background_compile_thread(isolate, source,
3780 script_details);
3781
3782 UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags_copy =
3783 background_compile_thread.data()->task->flags();
3784
3785 CHECK(background_compile_thread.Start());
3786 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> main_thread_maybe_result;
3787 bool main_thread_had_stack_overflow = false;
3788 // In parallel, compile on the main thread to flush out any data races.
3789 {
3790 IsCompiledScope inner_is_compiled_scope;
3791 // The background thread should also create any relevant exceptions, so we
3792 // can ignore the main-thread created ones.
3793 // TODO(leszeks): Maybe verify that any thrown (or unthrown) exceptions are
3794 // equivalent.
3795 TryCatch ignore_try_catch(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate));
3796 flags_copy.set_script_id(Script::kTemporaryScriptId);
3797 main_thread_maybe_result = CompileScriptOnMainThread(
3798 flags_copy, source, script_details, NOT_NATIVES_CODE, nullptr, isolate,
3799 MaybeHandle<Script>(), &inner_is_compiled_scope);
3800 if (main_thread_maybe_result.is_null()) {
3801 // Assume all range errors are stack overflows.
3802 main_thread_had_stack_overflow = CompilationExceptionIsRangeError(
3803 isolate, direct_handle(isolate->exception(), isolate));
3804 isolate->clear_exception();
3805 }
3806 }
3807
3808 // Join with background thread and finalize compilation.
3809 background_compile_thread.ParkedJoin(isolate->main_thread_local_isolate());
3810
3811 ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails compilation_details;
3812 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result =
3813 Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForStreamedScript(
3814 isolate, source, script_details, background_compile_thread.data(),
3815 &compilation_details);
3816
3817 // Either both compiles should succeed, or both should fail. The one exception
3818 // to this is that the main-thread compilation might stack overflow while the
3819 // background compilation doesn't, so relax the check to include this case.
3820 // TODO(leszeks): Compare the contents of the results of the two compiles.
3821 if (main_thread_had_stack_overflow) {
3822 CHECK(main_thread_maybe_result.is_null());
3823 } else {
3824 CHECK_EQ(maybe_result.is_null(), main_thread_maybe_result.is_null());
3825 }
3826
3827 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
3828 if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
3829 // The BackgroundCompileTask's IsCompiledScope will keep the result alive
3830 // until it dies at the end of this function, after which this new
3831 // IsCompiledScope can take over.
3832 *is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
3833 }
3834
3835 return maybe_result;
3836}
3837
3838namespace {
3839ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult CategorizeLookupResult(
3840 const CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult& lookup_result) {
3841 return !lookup_result.toplevel_sfi().is_null()
3842 ? ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult::kHit
3843 : !lookup_result.script().is_null()
3844 ? ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult::kPartial
3845 : ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult::kMiss;
3846}
3847} // namespace
3848
3849MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptImpl(
3850 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> source,
3851 const ScriptDetails& script_details, v8::Extension* extension,
3852 AlignedCachedData* cached_data, BackgroundDeserializeTask* deserialize_task,
3853 v8::CompileHintCallback compile_hint_callback,
3854 void* compile_hint_callback_data,
3855 ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions compile_options,
3856 ScriptCompiler::NoCacheReason no_cache_reason, NativesFlag natives,
3857 ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails* compilation_details) {
3858 ScriptCompileTimerScope compile_timer(isolate, no_cache_reason,
3859 compilation_details);
3860
3861 if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache) {
3862 // Have to have exactly one of cached_data or deserialize_task.
3863 DCHECK(cached_data || deserialize_task);
3864 DCHECK(!(cached_data && deserialize_task));
3865 DCHECK_NULL(extension);
3866 } else {
3867 DCHECK_NULL(cached_data);
3868 DCHECK_NULL(deserialize_task);
3869 }
3870
3871 if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCompileHints) {
3872 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(compile_hint_callback);
3873 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(compile_hint_callback_data);
3874 } else {
3875 DCHECK_NULL(compile_hint_callback);
3876 DCHECK_NULL(compile_hint_callback_data);
3877 }
3878
3879 compilation_details->background_time_in_microseconds =
3880 deserialize_task ? deserialize_task->background_time_in_microseconds()
3881 : 0;
3882
3883 LanguageMode language_mode = construct_language_mode(v8_flags.use_strict);
3884 CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
3885
3886 // For extensions or REPL mode scripts neither do a compilation cache lookup,
3887 // nor put the compilation result back into the cache.
3888 const bool use_compilation_cache =
3889 extension == nullptr && script_details.repl_mode == REPLMode::kNo;
3890 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
3891 MaybeHandle<Script> maybe_script;
3892 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
3893 if (use_compilation_cache) {
3894 bool can_consume_code_cache =
3895 compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache;
3896 if (can_consume_code_cache) {
3897 compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache();
3898 }
3899
3900 // First check per-isolate compilation cache.
3901 CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
3902 compilation_cache->LookupScript(source, script_details, language_mode);
3903 compilation_details->in_memory_cache_result =
3904 CategorizeLookupResult(lookup_result);
3905 maybe_script = lookup_result.script();
3906 maybe_result = lookup_result.toplevel_sfi();
3907 is_compiled_scope = lookup_result.is_compiled_scope();
3908 if (!maybe_result.is_null()) {
3909 compile_timer.set_hit_isolate_cache();
3910 } else if (can_consume_code_cache) {
3911 compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache();
3912 // Then check cached code provided by embedder.
3913 NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(
3914 isolate->counters()->compile_deserialize());
3915 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileDeserialize);
3916 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
3917 "V8.CompileDeserialize");
3918 if (deserialize_task) {
3919 // If there's a cache consume task, finish it.
3920 maybe_result =
3921 deserialize_task->Finish(isolate, source, script_details);
3922 // It is possible at this point that there is a Script object for this
3923 // script in the compilation cache (held in the variable maybe_script),
3924 // which does not match maybe_result->script(). This could happen any of
3925 // three ways:
3926 // 1. The embedder didn't call MergeWithExistingScript.
3927 // 2. At the time the embedder called SourceTextAvailable, there was not
3928 // yet a Script in the compilation cache, but it arrived sometime
3929 // later.
3930 // 3. At the time the embedder called SourceTextAvailable, there was a
3931 // Script available, and the new content has been merged into that
3932 // Script. However, since then, the Script was replaced in the
3933 // compilation cache, such as by another evaluation of the script
3934 // hitting case 2, or DevTools clearing the cache.
3935 // This is okay; the new Script object will replace the current Script
3936 // held by the compilation cache. Both Scripts may remain in use
3937 // indefinitely, causing increased memory usage, but these cases are
3938 // sufficiently unlikely, and ensuring a correct merge in the third case
3939 // would be non-trivial.
3940 } else {
3941 maybe_result = CodeSerializer::Deserialize(
3942 isolate, cached_data, source, script_details, maybe_script);
3943 }
3944
3945 bool consuming_code_cache_succeeded = false;
3946 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
3947 if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
3948 is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
3949 if (is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) {
3950 consuming_code_cache_succeeded = true;
3951 // Promote to per-isolate compilation cache.
3952 compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
3953 }
3954 }
3955 if (!consuming_code_cache_succeeded) {
3956 // Deserializer failed. Fall through to compile.
3957 compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache_failed();
3958 }
3959 }
3960 }
3961
3962 if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
3963 // No cache entry found compile the script.
3964 if (v8_flags.stress_background_compile &&
3965 CanBackgroundCompile(script_details, extension, compile_options,
3966 natives)) {
3967 // If the --stress-background-compile flag is set, do the actual
3968 // compilation on a background thread, and wait for its result.
3969 maybe_result = CompileScriptOnBothBackgroundAndMainThread(
3970 source, script_details, isolate, &is_compiled_scope);
3971 } else {
3972 UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
3973 UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForToplevelCompile(
3974 isolate, natives == NOT_NATIVES_CODE, language_mode,
3975 script_details.repl_mode,
3976 script_details.origin_options.IsModule() ? ScriptType::kModule
3977 : ScriptType::kClassic,
3978 v8_flags.lazy);
3979
3980 flags.set_is_eager(compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile);
3981 flags.set_compile_hints_magic_enabled(
3982 compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kFollowCompileHintsMagicComment);
3983
3984 if (DirectHandle<Script> script; maybe_script.ToHandle(&script)) {
3985 flags.set_script_id(script->id());
3986 }
3987
3988 maybe_result = CompileScriptOnMainThread(
3989 flags, source, script_details, natives, extension, isolate,
3990 maybe_script, &is_compiled_scope, compile_hint_callback,
3991 compile_hint_callback_data);
3992 }
3993
3994 // Add the result to the isolate cache.
3995 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
3996 if (use_compilation_cache && maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
3997 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
3998 compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
3999 } else if (maybe_result.is_null() && natives != EXTENSION_CODE) {
4000 isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
4001 }
4002 }
4003 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4004 if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions::kProduceCompileHints &&
4005 maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4006 Cast<Script>(result->script())->set_produce_compile_hints(true);
4007 }
4008
4009 return maybe_result;
4010}

4078// static
4079MaybeHandle<JSFunction> Compiler::GetWrappedFunction(
4080 Handle<String> source, DirectHandle<Context> context,
4081 const ScriptDetails& script_details, AlignedCachedData* cached_data,
4082 v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions compile_options,
4083 v8::ScriptCompiler::NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
4084 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
4085 ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails compilation_details;
4086 ScriptCompileTimerScope compile_timer(isolate, no_cache_reason,
4087 &compilation_details);
4088
4089 if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache) {
4090 DCHECK(cached_data);
4091 DCHECK_EQ(script_details.repl_mode, REPLMode::kNo);
4092 } else {
4093 DCHECK_NULL(cached_data);
4094 }
4095
4096 LanguageMode language_mode = construct_language_mode(v8_flags.use_strict);
4097 DCHECK(!script_details.wrapped_arguments.is_null());
4098 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
4099 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4100 Handle<Script> script;
4101 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
4102 bool can_consume_code_cache =
4103 compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache;
4104 CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
4105 // First check per-isolate compilation cache.
4106 CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
4107 compilation_cache->LookupScript(source, script_details, language_mode);
4108 maybe_result = lookup_result.toplevel_sfi();
4109 if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4110 is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4111 compile_timer.set_hit_isolate_cache();
4112 } else if (can_consume_code_cache) {
4113 compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache();
4114 // Then check cached code provided by embedder.
4115 NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(isolate->counters()->compile_deserialize());
4116 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileDeserialize);
4117 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4118 "V8.CompileDeserialize");
4119 maybe_result = CodeSerializer::Deserialize(isolate, cached_data, source,
4120 script_details);
4121 bool consuming_code_cache_succeeded = false;
4122 if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4123 is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4124 if (is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) {
4125 consuming_code_cache_succeeded = true;
4126 // Promote to per-isolate compilation cache.
4127 compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
4128 }
4129 }
4130 if (!consuming_code_cache_succeeded) {
4131 // Deserializer failed. Fall through to compile.
4132 compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache_failed();
4133 }
4134 }
4135
4136 if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
4137 UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags = UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForToplevelCompile(
4138 isolate, true, language_mode, script_details.repl_mode,
4139 ScriptType::kClassic, v8_flags.lazy);
4140 flags.set_is_eval(true); // Use an eval scope as declaration scope.
4141 flags.set_function_syntax_kind(FunctionSyntaxKind::kWrapped);
4142 // TODO(delphick): Remove this and instead make the wrapped and wrapper
4143 // functions fully non-lazy instead thus preventing source positions from
4144 // being omitted.
4145 flags.set_collect_source_positions(true);
4146 flags.set_is_eager(compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile);
4147
4148 UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
4149 ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
4150 ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
4151
4152 MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info;
4153 if (!IsNativeContext(*context)) {
4154 maybe_outer_scope_info = direct_handle(context->scope_info(), isolate);
4155 }
4156 script = NewScript(isolate, &parse_info, source, script_details,
4157 NOT_NATIVES_CODE);
4158
4159 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> top_level;
4160 maybe_result = v8::internal::CompileToplevel(&parse_info, script,
4161 maybe_outer_scope_info,
4162 isolate, &is_compiled_scope);
4163 if (maybe_result.is_null()) isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
4164 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, top_level, maybe_result);
4165
4166 SharedFunctionInfo::ScriptIterator infos(isolate, *script);
4167 for (Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> info = infos.Next(); !info.is_null();
4168 info = infos.Next()) {
4169 if (info->is_wrapped()) {
4170 result = direct_handle(info, isolate);
4171 break;
4172 }
4173 }
4174 DCHECK(!result.is_null());
4175
4176 is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4177 script = Handle<Script>(Cast<Script>(result->script()), isolate);
4178 // Add the result to the isolate cache if there's no context extension.
4179 if (maybe_outer_scope_info.is_null()) {
4180 compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
4181 }
4182 }
4183
4184 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
4185
4186 return Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, result, context}
4187 .set_allocation_type(AllocationType::kYoung)
4188 .Build();
4189}

4191// static
4192MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>
4193Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForStreamedScript(
4194 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> source,
4195 const ScriptDetails& script_details, ScriptStreamingData* streaming_data,
4196 ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails* compilation_details) {
4197 DCHECK(!script_details.origin_options.IsWasm());
4198
4199 ScriptCompileTimerScope compile_timer(
4200 isolate, ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource,
4201 compilation_details);
4202 PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
4203
4204 BackgroundCompileTask* task = streaming_data->task.get();
4205
4206 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
4207 MaybeDirectHandle<Script> maybe_cached_script;
4208 // Check if compile cache already holds the SFI, if so no need to finalize
4209 // the code compiled on the background thread.
4210 CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
4211 {
4212 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4213 "V8.StreamingFinalization.CheckCache");
4214 CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
4215 compilation_cache->LookupScript(source, script_details,
4216 task->flags().outer_language_mode());
4217 compilation_details->in_memory_cache_result =
4218 CategorizeLookupResult(lookup_result);
4219
4220 if (!lookup_result.toplevel_sfi().is_null()) {
4221 maybe_result = lookup_result.toplevel_sfi();
4222 }
4223
4224 if (!maybe_result.is_null()) {
4225 compile_timer.set_hit_isolate_cache();
4226 } else {
4227 maybe_cached_script = lookup_result.script();
4228 }
4229 }
4230
4231 if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
4232 // No cache entry found, finalize compilation of the script and add it to
4233 // the isolate cache.
4234 RCS_SCOPE(isolate,
4235 RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompilePublishBackgroundFinalization);
4236 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4237 "V8.OffThreadFinalization.Publish");
4238
4239 maybe_result = task->FinalizeScript(isolate, source, script_details,
4240 maybe_cached_script);
4241
4242 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4243 if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4244 if (task->flags().produce_compile_hints()) {
4245 Cast<Script>(result->script())->set_produce_compile_hints(true);
4246 }
4247
4248 // Add compiled code to the isolate cache.
4249 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4250 "V8.StreamingFinalization.AddToCache");
4251 compilation_cache->PutScript(source, task->flags().outer_language_mode(),
4252 result);
4253 }
4254 }
4255
4256 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4257 "V8.StreamingFinalization.Release");
4258 streaming_data->Release();
4259 return maybe_result;

4262// static
4263template <typename IsolateT>
4264DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(
4265 FunctionLiteral* literal, Handle<Script> script, IsolateT* isolate) {
4266 // If we're parallel compiling functions, we might already have attached a SFI
4267 // to this literal.
4268 if (!literal->shared_function_info().is_null()) {
4269 return literal->shared_function_info();
4270 }
4271 // Precondition: code has been parsed and scopes have been analyzed.
4272 MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_existing;
4273
4274 // Find any previously allocated shared function info for the given literal.
4275 maybe_existing = Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(script, isolate, literal);
4276
4277 // If we found an existing shared function info, return it.
4278 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> existing;
4279 if (maybe_existing.ToHandle(&existing)) {
4280 // If the function has been uncompiled (bytecode flushed) it will have lost
4281 // any preparsed data. If we produced preparsed data during this compile for
4282 // this function, replace the uncompiled data with one that includes it.
4283 if (literal->produced_preparse_data() != nullptr &&
4284 existing->HasUncompiledDataWithoutPreparseData()) {
4285 DirectHandle<UncompiledData> existing_uncompiled_data(
4286 existing->uncompiled_data(isolate), isolate);
4287 DCHECK_EQ(literal->start_position(),
4288 existing_uncompiled_data->start_position());
4289 DCHECK_EQ(literal->end_position(),
4290 existing_uncompiled_data->end_position());
4291 // Use existing uncompiled data's inferred name as it may be more
4292 // accurate than the literal we preparsed.
4293 Handle<String> inferred_name =
4294 handle(existing_uncompiled_data->inferred_name(), isolate);
4295 Handle<PreparseData> preparse_data =
4296 literal->produced_preparse_data()->Serialize(isolate);
4297 DirectHandle<UncompiledData> new_uncompiled_data =
4298 isolate->factory()->NewUncompiledDataWithPreparseData(
4299 inferred_name, existing_uncompiled_data->start_position(),
4300 existing_uncompiled_data->end_position(), preparse_data);
4301 existing->set_uncompiled_data(*new_uncompiled_data);
4302 }
4303 return existing;
4304 }
4305
4306 // Allocate a shared function info object which will be compiled lazily.
4307 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result =
4308 isolate->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForLiteral(literal, script,
4309 false);
4310 return result;
4311}

4318// static
4319MaybeHandle<Code> Compiler::CompileOptimizedOSR(
4320 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
4321 BytecodeOffset osr_offset, ConcurrencyMode mode, CodeKind code_kind) {
4322 DCHECK(IsOSR(osr_offset));
4323
4324 if (V8_UNLIKELY(isolate->serializer_enabled())) return {};
4325 if (V8_UNLIKELY(function->shared()->optimization_disabled())) return {};
4326
4327 // TODO(chromium:1031479): Currently, OSR triggering mechanism is tied to the
4328 // bytecode array. So, it might be possible to mark closure in one native
4329 // context and optimize a closure from a different native context. So check if
4330 // there is a feedback vector before OSRing. We don't expect this to happen
4331 // often.
4332 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!function->has_feedback_vector())) return {};
4333
4334 CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRStarted(isolate, function, osr_offset, mode);
4335 MaybeHandle<Code> result =
4336 GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, mode, code_kind, osr_offset);
4337
4338 if (result.is_null()) {
4339 CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRUnavailable(isolate, function, osr_offset,
4340 mode);
4341 } else {
4342 DCHECK_GE(result.ToHandleChecked()->kind(), CodeKind::MAGLEV);
4343 CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRAvailable(isolate, function, osr_offset,
4344 mode);
4345 }
4346
4347 return result;
4348}
