4357// static
4358void Compiler::FinalizeTurbofanCompilationJob(TurbofanCompilationJob* job,
4359 Isolate* isolate) {
4360 VMState<COMPILER> state(isolate);
4361 OptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
4362
4363 TimerEventScope<TimerEventRecompileSynchronous> timer(isolate);
4364 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeConcurrentFinalize);
4365 TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4366 "V8.OptimizeConcurrentFinalize", job->trace_id(),
4367 TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN);
4368
4369 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = compilation_info->closure();
4370 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = compilation_info->shared_info();
4371
4372 const bool use_result = !compilation_info->discard_result_for_testing();
4373 const BytecodeOffset osr_offset = compilation_info->osr_offset();
4374
4375 DCHECK(!shared->HasBreakInfo(isolate));
4376
4377 // 1) Optimization on the concurrent thread may have failed.
4378 // 2) The function may have already been optimized by OSR. Simply continue.
4379 // Except when OSR already disabled optimization for some reason.
4380 // 3) The code may have already been invalidated due to dependency change.
4381 // 4) InstructionStream generation may have failed.
4382 if (job->state() == CompilationJob::State::kReadyToFinalize) {
4383 if (shared->optimization_disabled()) {
4384 job->RetryOptimization(BailoutReason::kOptimizationDisabled);
4385 } else if (job->FinalizeJob(isolate) == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
4386 job->RecordCompilationStats(ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent, isolate);
4387 job->RecordFunctionCompilation(LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction,
4388 isolate);
4389 if (V8_LIKELY(use_result)) {
4390 function->SetTieringInProgress(false,
4391 job->compilation_info()->osr_offset());
4392 if (!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL || IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
4393 OptimizedCodeCache::Insert(
4394 isolate, *compilation_info->closure(),
4395 compilation_info->osr_offset(), *compilation_info->code(),
4396 compilation_info->function_context_specializing());
4397 }
4398 CompilerTracer::TraceCompletedJob(isolate, compilation_info);
4399 if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
4400 CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRFinished(isolate, function,
4401 osr_offset);
4402 } else {
4403 function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, *compilation_info->code());
4404 }
4405 }
4406 return;
4407 }
4408 }
4409
4410 DCHECK_EQ(job->state(), CompilationJob::State::kFailed);
4411 CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
4412 job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
4413 job->finalize_in_ms());
4414 if (V8_LIKELY(use_result)) {
4415 function->SetTieringInProgress(false,
4416 job->compilation_info()->osr_offset());
4417 if (!IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
4418 function->UpdateCode(shared->GetCode(isolate));
4419 }
4420 }
4421}

4491// static
4492void Compiler::PostInstantiation(Isolate* isolate,
4493 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
4494 IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
4495 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(), isolate);
4496
4497 // If code is compiled to bytecode (i.e., isn't asm.js), then allocate a
4498 // feedback and check for optimized code.
4499 if (is_compiled_scope->is_compiled() && shared->HasBytecodeArray()) {
4500 // Don't reset budget if there is a closure feedback cell array already. We
4501 // are just creating a new closure that shares the same feedback cell.
4502 JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(function, is_compiled_scope, false);
4503
4504#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4505 if (function->has_feedback_vector()) {
4506 // Evict any deoptimized code on feedback vector. We need to do this after
4507 // creating the closure, since any heap allocations could trigger a GC and
4508 // deoptimized the code on the feedback vector. So check for any
4509 // deoptimized code just before installing it on the funciton.
4510 function->feedback_vector()->EvictOptimizedCodeMarkedForDeoptimization(
4511 isolate, *shared, "new function from shared function info");
4512 Tagged<Code> code = function->feedback_vector()->optimized_code(isolate);
4513 if (!code.is_null()) {
4514 // Caching of optimized code enabled and optimized code found.
4515 DCHECK(!code->marked_for_deoptimization());
4516 DCHECK(function->shared()->is_compiled());
4517 function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, code);
4518 }
4519 }
4520#endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4521
4522 if (v8_flags.always_turbofan && shared->allows_lazy_compilation() &&
4523 !shared->optimization_disabled() &&
4524 !function->HasAvailableOptimizedCode(isolate)) {
4525 CompilerTracer::TraceMarkForAlwaysOpt(isolate, function);
4526 JSFunction::EnsureFeedbackVector(isolate, function, is_compiled_scope);
4527 function->RequestOptimization(isolate, CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS,
4528 ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
4529 }
4530 }
4531
4532 if (shared->is_toplevel() || shared->is_wrapped()) {
4533 // If it's a top-level script, report compilation to the debugger.
4534 DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate);
4535 isolate->debug()->OnAfterCompile(script);
4536 TRACE_EVENT1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown"),
4537 "ScriptCompiled", "data",
4538 AddScriptCompiledTrace(isolate, shared));
4539 bool tracing_enabled;
4540 TRACE_EVENT_CATEGORY_GROUP_ENABLED(
4541 TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown-sources"),
4542 &tracing_enabled);
4543 if (tracing_enabled) {
4544 EmitScriptSourceTextTrace(isolate, shared);
4545 }
4546 }

4589void Compiler::EmitScriptSourceTextTrace(
4590 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
4591 DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate);
4592 if (IsString(script->source())) {
4593 Tagged<String> source = i::Cast<i::String>(script->source());
4594 auto script_id = script->id();
4595 auto isolate_string = std::to_string(reinterpret_cast<size_t>(isolate));
4596 int32_t source_length = source->length();
4597 const int32_t kSplitMaxLength = 1000000;
4598 if (source_length <= kSplitMaxLength) {
4599 auto value = v8::tracing::TracedValue::Create();
4600 value->SetString("isolate", isolate_string);
4601 value->SetInteger("scriptId", script_id);
4602 value->SetInteger("length", source_length);
4603 value->SetString("sourceText", source->ToCString().get());
4604 TRACE_EVENT1(
4605 TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown-sources"),
4606 "ScriptCompiled", "data", std::move(value));
4607 } else {
4608 Handle<String> handle_source(source, isolate);
4609 int32_t split_count = source_length / kSplitMaxLength + 1;
4610 for (int32_t i = 0; i < split_count; i++) {
4611 int32_t begin = i * kSplitMaxLength;
4612 int32_t end = std::min(begin + kSplitMaxLength, source_length);
4613 DirectHandle<String> partial_source =
4614 isolate->factory()->NewSubString(handle_source, begin, end);
4615 auto split_trace_value = v8::tracing::TracedValue::Create();
4616 split_trace_value->SetInteger("splitIndex", i);
4617 split_trace_value->SetInteger("splitCount", split_count);
4618 split_trace_value->SetString("isolate", isolate_string);
4619 split_trace_value->SetInteger("scriptId", script_id);
4620 split_trace_value->SetString("sourceText",
4621 partial_source->ToCString().get());
4622 TRACE_EVENT1(
4623 TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown-sources"),
4624 "LargeScriptCompiledSplits", "data", std::move(split_trace_value));
4625 }
4626 }
4627 }
